<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#160;</p>

<td valign="top"  style="width:15.58%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><img src="gycirsmwh4vw000002.jpg" title="" alt="" style="width:102px;height:150px;"></p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="width:32.42%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#5A2D82;font-size:16pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Letter from our Chairman and Chief Executive Officer</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="width:4%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:-1pt;;text-indent:1pt;;font-size:10.5pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="width:15.34%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><img src="gycirsmwh4vw000003.jpg" title="" alt="" style="width:102px;height:150px;"></p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="width:32.66%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#5A2D82;font-size:16pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Letter from our </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#5A2D82;font-size:16pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Lead Director</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10.5pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan="2" valign="top"  style="width:48%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">March 29, 2019</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:4pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Dear Fellow Shareholders,</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:4pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Thank you for your investment in Mondel&#275;z International and for your continued support as we enter a new phase in the growth of our six-year-young company. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:4pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">I&#8217;m pleased with our progress in 2018. After five years of a more cost-driven approach, we have started to shift more of our attention to top-line growth, which started to show signs of acceleration during the year. We also formulated a new long-term strategy and took meaningful steps forward in our mission to lead the future of snacking around the world. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:4pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Mondel&#275;z International is a global leader in snacking, which is an attractive market, distinct from packaged foods, with strong growth and approximately $1.2 trillion in annual global consumer spending. Our new purpose as a company &#8211;&nbsp;&nbsp;to empower people to snack right &#8211; has led us to take an in-depth look at consumers around the world and how their snacking behavior is evolving. It also guided our development of a new long-term strategy with well-defined priorities that will accelerate growth and generate shareholder value while creating a sustainable business with a positive impact on people and the planet.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:8pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">LONG-TERM PRIORITIES</p>
<p style="margin-top:4pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Following a comprehensive review during my first full year as CEO, we introduced a new long-term strategy that builds on our many advantages as a company. These include our leadership positions in the high-growth snacking categories, powerful global brands and local jewels, a real global presence, particularly in emerging markets, a strong value chain enabled by productivity initiatives and investments, and our talented people. </p>
<p style="margin-top:4pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">To best leverage these strengths, our new strategic plan aims to:</p>
<p style="margin-top:4pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:27.35pt;;text-indent:-18.35pt;;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman'">&#8226;</font><font style="font-weight:bold;font-family:Arial;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Accelerate Consumer-Centric Growth. </font><font style="font-family:Arial;">We are adopting a new, more consumer-centric commercial approach that we believe will create more demand for our beloved global and local brands. It includes increasing our understanding of consumers through a set of proprietary insights about snacking behaviors and occasions that will allow us to target our investments in the areas of highest growth potential.</font></p>
<p style="margin-top:4pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:36.35pt;;text-indent:-18.35pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:1pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="width:4%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:-1pt;;text-indent:1pt;;font-size:10.5pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td colspan="2" valign="top"  style="width:48%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">March 29, 2019</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:4pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Dear Fellow Shareholders,</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:4pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Our Board is deeply committed to independent oversight and strong corporate governance to maximize the value of your investment. I&#8217;m honored that my fellow independent directors have selected me to serve as independent Lead Director, and I will continue to work hard to foster shareholder engagement and Board oversight and effectiveness. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:4pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We are very pleased with the Company&#8217;s achievements in 2018, beginning with our leadership transition to new CEO Dirk Van de Put and the completion of a rigorous strategic review of the Company&#8217;s operations. We executed seamlessly on our leadership succession, including Dirk&#8217;s transition into the additional role of Chairman and Luca Zaramella&#8217;s assumption of the CFO role. I am particularly pleased that amidst all those changes we delivered strong financial results. Throughout the strategic review, the Board and management team worked in close coordination to craft a consumer-centric strategy that leverages our Company&#8217;s unique strengths in the attractive snacking market to accelerate growth. </p>
<p style="margin-top:4pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We are proud of our directors&#8217; diverse backgrounds and considerable leadership experience at global companies. Our collective skill set &#8211; strategic planning, international operations, manufacturing, consumer products, marketing, innovation, food services, technology, people development, capital investments, finance and research &#8211; and diverse perspectives enable highly effective Board oversight and rigorous decision-making. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:4pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">In 2018, we refreshed the Board with the addition of two directors, Debra Crew and Peter May, who each possess proven track records with global food and beverage companies as well as deep financial acumen, marketing and international experience. All our directors except Chairman &amp; CEO Dirk Van de Put are independent, and all committees are fully independent &#8211; an important feature of an effective Board. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:4pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">As independent Lead Director, I&#8217;m deeply engaged in my responsibilities, including the review and approval of the annual schedule of Board meetings, agenda topics, in addition to presiding at the meetings of independent directors in executive session. I chair the Governance, Membership and Public Affairs Committee and work to </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
</tr>
</table></div>
<p style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:1pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<div>
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="center" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top"  style="width:48%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:27.35pt;;text-indent:-18pt;;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman'">&#8226;</font><font style="font-weight:bold;font-family:Arial;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Drive Operational Excellence. </font><font style="font-family:Arial;">Ongoing cost and productivity focus remains fundamental to how we run the business. We are making incremental improvements to reduce our costs and have many initiatives underway to enhance our operations across sales, marketing and the supply chain.</font></p>
<p style="margin-top:4pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:27.35pt;;text-indent:-18.35pt;;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman'">&#8226;</font><font style="font-weight:bold;font-family:Arial;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Build a Winning Growth Culture. </font><font style="font-family:Arial;">We can only deliver on our growth opportunities by giving our people the tools, resources and incentives they need to perform at their very best. So, we are creating a winning growth culture that moves quickly, empowers our organization&#8217;s leaders at the local level, accelerates innovation and builds world-class capabilities across a diverse and inclusive workforce.</font></p>
<p style="margin-top:4pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The combination of our unique structural advantages and strategic plan gives us confidence that we can deliver on a new set of long-term financial targets and capital allocation priorities to create value for our shareholders, including: </p>
<p style="margin-top:4pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:31.85pt;;text-indent:-18.35pt;;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman'">&#8226;</font><font style="font-weight:bold;font-family:Arial;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;">Organic Net Revenue<sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(1)</sup> growth of 3 percent plus;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin-top:4pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:31.85pt;;text-indent:-18.35pt;;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman'">&#8226;</font><font style="font-weight:bold;font-family:Arial;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;">High-single digit Adjusted EPS<sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(1)</sup> growth at constant currency;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin-top:4pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:31.85pt;;text-indent:-18.35pt;;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman'">&#8226;</font><font style="font-weight:bold;font-family:Arial;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;">Free Cash Flow<sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(1) </sup>of $3 billion plus; and</font></p>
<p style="margin-top:4pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:31.85pt;;text-indent:-18.35pt;;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman'">&#8226;</font><font style="font-weight:bold;font-family:Arial;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;">Dividend growth outpacing Adjusted EPS growth. </font></p>
<p style="margin-top:8pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">A LOOK BACK AT OUR PROGRESS </p>
<p style="margin-top:4pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">I am particularly pleased with the progress we have made towards bringing our new plan to life. In 2018 we:</p>
<p style="margin-top:4pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:36pt;;text-indent:-18pt;;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman'">&#8226;</font><font style="font-weight:bold;font-family:Arial;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;">Launched a new approach to marketing, which includes more balanced investments in global and local brands and a completely new marketing playbook;</font></p>
<p style="margin-top:4pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:36.35pt;;text-indent:-18.35pt;;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman'">&#8226;</font><font style="font-weight:bold;font-family:Arial;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;">Deployed a &#8216;test, learn and scale&#8217; approach to innovation in our local business units;</font></p>
<p style="margin-top:4pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:36.35pt;;text-indent:-18.35pt;;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman'">&#8226;</font><font style="font-weight:bold;font-family:Arial;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;">Launched our SnackFutures innovation and venture hub;</font></p>
<p style="margin-top:4pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:36pt;;text-indent:-18pt;;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman'">&#8226;</font><font style="font-weight:bold;font-family:Arial;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;">Acquired the Tate&#8217;s premium biscuits business;</font></p>
<p style="margin-top:4pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:36.35pt;;text-indent:-18.35pt;;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman'">&#8226;</font><font style="font-weight:bold;font-family:Arial;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;">Improved sales and route-to-market execution while delivering continued productivity improvements;</font></p>
<p style="margin-top:4pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:36.35pt;;text-indent:-18.35pt;;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman'">&#8226;</font><font style="font-weight:bold;font-family:Arial;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;">Improved service levels in North America and achieved highest-ever service levels in Europe;</font></p>
<p style="margin-top:4pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:36.35pt;;text-indent:-18.35pt;;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman'">&#8226;</font><font style="font-weight:bold;font-family:Arial;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;">Launched a new local-first commercial model to reduce complexity and increase speed; and </font></p>
<p style="margin-top:4pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:36.35pt;;text-indent:-18.35pt;;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman'">&#8226;</font><font style="font-weight:bold;font-family:Arial;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;">Changed our incentive structure to include volume-driven growth and absolute profit-dollar growth metrics, as well as quality of results.</font></p>
<p style="margin-top:4pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">These initiatives helped us deliver on all our financial commitments in 2018, including strong earnings growth, free cash flow and capital return to shareholders: </p>
<p style="margin-top:4pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:36.35pt;;text-indent:-18.35pt;;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman'">&#8226;</font><font style="font-weight:bold;font-family:Arial;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;">Net revenues increased 0.2 percent; Organic Net Revenue<sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(2)</sup> grew 2.4 percent;</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:4pt;margin-left:36pt;;text-indent:-18pt;;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman'">&#8226;</font><font style="font-weight:bold;font-family:Arial;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;">Diluted Earnings Per Share were $2.28, up 23 percent; Adjusted EPS<sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(2)</sup> was $2.43, up 15 percent on a constant currency basis;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="width:4%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:-1pt;;text-indent:1pt;;font-size:10.5pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="width:48%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">develop recommendations for committee structure, membership, rotations and chairs. I lead an annual Board, committee and director self-assessment process to identify opportunities for improvement, and I&#8217;m available for consultation with the Company&#8217;s major shareholders.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:4pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Attracting, retaining and rewarding top talent through the Company&#8217;s compensation programs is critical to our success and a top priority of the Board. Our compensation program is, and has always been, strongly performance-based and aligned with shareholders&#8217; interests. Following the say-on-pay vote last year, we carefully reviewed our compensation policies and engaged with investors to understand their perspectives. Based on conversations with major shareholders, we confirmed that the key drivers of last year&#8217;s vote were one-time issues related to our leadership transition &#8211; primarily the make-whole awards for our new CEO. Securing executive talent with a proven track record of success always comes with a cost, and the Board was confident in offering Dirk Van de Put substantial make-whole awards, most of which were in the form of company equity, as an investment in our future. The Company&#8217;s performance so far under Dirk&#8217;s leadership including in 2018 reinforces our confidence in the decision to bring him aboard to develop and execute our growth strategy. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:4pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We are committed to closely linking all executives&#8217; compensation to performance in a manner that supports the new strategy that Dirk is leading, and that is in line with comparable peers and best practices in corporate governance. The Board and Human Resources and Compensation Committee are also conducting in-depth analysis of our leaders and their future potential as part of our ongoing succession planning.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:4pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">In addition to its oversight and engagement in our strategic direction, business performance, acquisitions and divestitures and talent management, the Board is heavily involved in the Company&#8217;s commitment to create a positive impact on the world while driving business performance. Mondel&#275;z International&#8217;s Sustainable and Mindful Snacking strategies bring together our environmental sustainability, consumer well-being, community engagement and safety projects and connect them to our business strategy in service of growth. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:4pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">I hope you will find our proxy statement and website to be useful resources to learn more about your Board, our corporate governance practices and policies and our sustainability and Impact initiatives. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:4pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We take very seriously the trust you place in us through your investment in Mondel&#275;z International. Your vote is important to us. We encourage you to read both our proxy statement and annual report in full and to vote in accordance with our recommendations. On behalf of all the directors, thank you for your continued support and investment in our Company.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:4pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Sincerely,</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><img src="gycirsmwh4vw000004.jpg" title="" alt="" style="width:93px;height:20px;"></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Joseph Neubauer</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
</tr>
</table></div>
<p style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:1pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:1pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<div>
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="center" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top"  style="width:48%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:36.35pt;;text-indent:-18.35pt;;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman'">&#8226;</font><font style="font-weight:bold;font-family:Arial;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;">Cash provided by operating activities was $3.9 billion, Free Cash Flow<sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(2)</sup> was $2.9 billion; and</font></p>
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:36.35pt;;text-indent:-18.35pt;;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman'">&#8226;</font><font style="font-weight:bold;font-family:Arial;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;">We returned $3.4 billion in capital to our shareholders through dividends and share repurchases; since the spin six years ago, we have returned more than $21 billion to our shareholders.</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We exited the year with solid momentum and are increasing targeted investments in 2019 in support of a sustainable acceleration in long-term growth. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">SUSTAINABLE AND MINDFUL SNACKING</p>
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">I am particularly proud that we continue to operate our business the right way, with a positive impact where people and the planet thrive. In 2018 we proudly: </p>
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:36pt;;text-indent:-18pt;;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman'">&#8226;</font><font style="font-weight:bold;font-family:Arial;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Committed to Making All Packaging Recyclable by 2025. </font><font style="font-family:Arial;">As a part of this commitment, all paper-based packaging will be sustainably sourced by 2020 and 65 million kg of packaging material worldwide will be eliminated by 2020.</font></p>
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:36pt;;text-indent:-18pt;;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman'">&#8226;</font><font style="font-weight:bold;font-family:Arial;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Expanded Harmony Sustainable Wheat Program. </font><font style="font-family:Arial;">We are scaling our sustainable wheat sourcing initiative to cover 100 percent of biscuit brands in the European Union by 2022. </font></p>
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:36pt;;text-indent:-18pt;;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman'">&#8226;</font><font style="font-weight:bold;font-family:Arial;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Added </font><font style="font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-family:Arial;">Milka</font><font style="font-weight:bold;font-family:Arial;"> Chocolate to Cocoa Life Sustainable Sourcing Program. </font><font style="font-family:Arial;">One of our largest chocolate brands, </font><font style="font-style:italic;font-family:Arial;">Milka</font><font style="font-family:Arial;">, joined Cocoa Life as part of our commitment to source all our cocoa sustainably over time. </font></p>
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:36pt;;text-indent:-18pt;;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman'">&#8226;</font><font style="font-weight:bold;font-family:Arial;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Increased Percentage of Portion Control Options in Our Portfolio. </font><font style="font-family:Arial;">Smaller portions help encourage mindful consumption and we are well on-track to reach our target of 15 percent of the portfolio.</font></p>
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:36pt;;text-indent:-18pt;;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman'">&#8226;</font><font style="font-weight:bold;font-family:Arial;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Announced Ambitious Sugar Reduction Program in the United Kingdom.</font><font style="font-family:Arial;"> A new </font><font style="font-style:italic;font-family:Arial;">Cadbury Dairy Milk</font><font style="font-family:Arial;"> bar with 30 percent less sugar will be launched in the United Kingdom, offering consumers greater choice and helping them to manage their sugar intake.</font></p>
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">You can find more information about our Impact efforts on our website, including our commitments related to safety, sustainability, well-being snacks and serving the communities in which we operate. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">LOOKING AHEAD </p>
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">I remain excited to lead an organization that is well-positioned and focused in its commitment to accelerate growth and create value for all our stakeholders &#8210; shareholders, consumers, customers, colleagues and communities around the world. I look forward to engaging with you in the months ahead as we continue to execute our long-term strategy. On behalf of all my colleagues at Mondel&#275;z International, thank you for your continued investment and support. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Best regards, </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><img src="gycirsmwh4vw000005.jpg" title="" alt="" style="width:117px;height:19px;"></p>
<p style="margin-top:3pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Dirk Van de Put</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Chairman &amp; CEO</p>
<p style="border-bottom:Solid 0.75pt #000000;padding-bottom:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(1) See definition in Annex A.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:9pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(2) See the GAAP to non-GAAP reconciliation in Annex A.</p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="width:4%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:-1pt;;text-indent:1pt;;font-size:10.5pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="width:48%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10.5pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU3"></a><font style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Forward-looking Statements</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">This proxy statement contains a number of forward-looking statements. Words, and variations of words, such as &#8220;will,&#8221; &#8220;expect,&#8221; &#8220;may,&#8221; &#8220;believe,&#8221; &#8220;intend,&#8221; &#8220;aim,&#8221; &#8220;deliver,&#8221; &#8220;target,&#8221; &#8220;commitment&#8221; and similar expressions are intended to identify our forward-looking statements, including, but not limited to, statements about: our future performance, including our future revenue growth, earnings per share and cash flow; our strategic plan to drive accelerated growth by adopting a more consumer-centric commercial approach, focusing on operational excellence and building a winning growth culture; demand for our brands; investments; cost discipline, including operational efficiency; our sustainable and mindful snacking initiatives; dividends; value creation for shareholders and other stakeholders; and our long-term financial targets. These forward-looking statements are subject to a number of risks and uncertainties, many of which are beyond our control, which could cause our actual results to differ materially from those indicated in our forward-looking statements. Such factors include, but are not limited to, risks from operating globally including in emerging markets; changes in currency exchange rates, controls and restrictions; continued volatility of commodity and other input costs; weakness in economic conditions; weakness in consumer spending; pricing actions; tax matters including changes in tax rates and laws, disagreements with taxing authorities and imposition of new taxes; use of information technology and third party service providers; unanticipated disruptions to our business, such as the malware incident, cyberattacks or other security breaches; competition; protection of our reputation and brand image; our ability to innovate and differentiate our products; the restructuring program and our other transformation initiatives not yielding the anticipated benefits; changes in the assumptions on which the restructuring program is based; management of our workforce; consolidation of retail customers and competition with retailer and other economy brands; changes in our relationships with suppliers or customers; legal, regulatory, tax or benefit law changes, claims or actions; strategic transactions; significant changes in valuation factors that may adversely affect our impairment testing of goodwill and intangible assets; perceived or actual product quality issues or product recalls; failure to maintain effective internal control over financial reporting; volatility of and access to capital or other markets; pension costs; and our ability to protect our intellectual property and intangible assets. Mondel&#275;z International disclaims and does not undertake any obligation to update or revise any forward-looking statement in this proxy statement, except as required by applicable law or regulation.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:12pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;color:#5A2D82;font-size:16pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU6"></a><a name="PROXY_STATEMENT_SUMMARY"></a><font style="color:#5A2D82;font-size:16pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="PROXY_STATEMENT_SUMMARY"></a>Proxy Statem</font><font style="color:#5A2D82;font-size:16pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">ent Summary </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">In this Proxy Statement Summary and throughout the Proxy Statement, &#8220;we,&#8221; &#8220;us,&#8221; &#8220;our,&#8221; &#8220;the Company&#8221; and &#8220;Mondel&#275;z International&#8221; refer to Mondel&#275;z International, Inc. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">This summary highlights select information contained elsewhere in this Proxy Statement. You should read the entire Proxy Statement carefully and consider all information in the Proxy Statement before voting. For more complete information regarding the Company&#8217;s 2018 performance, please see the Company&#8217;s Annual Report on Form 10-K for the year ended December&#160;31, 2018 (the &#8220;2018 Form 10-K&#8221;). </p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-family:Arial;font-size:12pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">2019 Annual Meeting of Shareholders (the &#8220;Annual Meeting&#8221;) </p>

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Governance, Membership and Public Affairs Committee (the &#8220;Governance Committee&#8221;) recommended and the Board of Directors (the &#8220;Board&#8221;) nominated each of the 13 incumbent directors listed here. The terms of all directors elected at the Annual Meeting will end at the 2020 Annual Meeting of Shareholders or when a director&#8217;s successor has been duly elected and qualified. Additional information about the director nominees is provided under &#8220;Election of Directors<font style="font-weight:bold;">&#160;&#8211;&#160;</font>Director Nominees for Election at the Annual Meeting.&#8221; </p>

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;color:#FFFFFF;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="Background-color:#5B2B82;">&#160;&#160;Proxy Statement Summary&#160;&#160;</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:6pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"></p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;color:#000000;font-family:Arial;font-size:12pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU9"></a><font style="font-weight:bold;color:#000000;font-family:Arial;font-size:12pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Our Strong Corporate Governance Framework Promotes the Long-Term Interests of Shareholders and Accountability and Trust in the Company</font><font style="font-weight:bold;color:#000000;font-family:Arial;font-size:12pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Our governance practices and polices enhance our Board&#8217;s effectiveness and accountability<font style="font-size:12pt;color:#000000;"> </font>and promote the Company&#8217;s long-term success. We highlight here key aspects of our corporate governance framework. Shareholders can find additional detail under &#8220;Corporate Governance&#8221; beginning on page 19, &#8220;Compensation Discussion and Analysis&#160;&#8211;&#160;Our Executive Compensation Governance Practices Reflect Best Practices to Protect and Promote our Shareholders&#8217; Interests&#8221; on page 45, and &#8220;2020 Annual Meeting of Shareholders&#8221; on page 95. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Arial;font-size:12pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#160;</p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr style="height:21.6pt;">
<td valign="middle"  BGCOLOR="#7030A0" style="width:46.88%; border-top:solid 1pt #FFFFFF; border-bottom:solid 1.5pt #FFFFFF; border-left:solid 1pt #FFFFFF; border-right:solid 1pt #FFFFFF;">
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#FFFFFF;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Key Practice/Policy</p></td>
<td valign="middle"  BGCOLOR="#7030A0" style="width:53.12%; border-top:solid 1pt #FFFFFF; border-bottom:solid 1.5pt #FFFFFF; border-left:solid 1pt #FFFFFF;">
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#FFFFFF;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Benefit to Board and Shareholders</p></td>
</tr>
<tr style="height:54pt;">
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" style="width:46.88%; border-bottom:solid 1pt #FFFFFF; border-left:solid 1pt #FFFFFF; border-right:solid 1pt #FFFFFF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Lead Director<font style="font-weight:normal;">. Independent Lead Director has substantive responsibilities:</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:13.5pt;;text-indent:-13.5pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;<font style="color:#000000;font-family:Arial;">engages in planning and approval of meeting schedules/agendas; </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:13.5pt;;text-indent:-13.5pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;<font style="color:#000000;font-family:Arial;">presides over frequent executive sessions of independent directors; and</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:13.5pt;;text-indent:-13.5pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;<font style="color:#000000;font-family:Arial;">consults with major shareholders,</font></p></td>
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" style="width:53.12%; border-bottom:solid 1pt #FFFFFF; border-left:solid 1pt #FFFFFF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">A highly effective and engaged Lead Director:</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:15.85pt;;text-indent:-13.7pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;<font style="color:#000000;font-family:Arial;">enhances independent directors&#8217; input and investors&#8217; perspectives on agendas and discussions;</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:15.85pt;;text-indent:-13.7pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;<font style="color:#000000;font-family:Arial;">fosters candid discussion during regular executive sessions of the independent directors; and</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:15.85pt;;text-indent:-13.7pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;<font style="color:#000000;font-family:Arial;">provides feedback to management regarding the Board&#8217;s concerns and information needs.</font></p></td>
</tr>
<tr style="height:27pt;">
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#E6E1EE" style="width:46.88%; border-bottom:solid 1pt #FFFFFF; border-left:solid 1pt #FFFFFF; border-right:solid 1pt #FFFFFF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Majority Independent Board<font style="font-weight:normal;">. Mondel&#275;z International requires that all non-management directors be independent. 12 of 13 directors are independent. </font></p></td>
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#E6E1EE" style="width:53.12%; border-bottom:solid 1pt #FFFFFF; border-left:solid 1pt #FFFFFF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Substantial majority of independent directors in the boardroom and fully independent committees effectively oversee management on behalf of shareholders.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr style="height:13.8pt;">
<td valign="middle"  BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" style="width:46.88%; border-bottom:solid 1pt #FFFFFF; border-left:solid 1pt #FFFFFF; border-right:solid 1pt #FFFFFF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Annual Elections<font style="font-weight:normal;">. Shareholders elect directors annually by majority vote.</font></p></td>
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" style="width:53.12%; border-bottom:solid 1pt #FFFFFF; border-left:solid 1pt #FFFFFF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Strengthens Board, committee and individual director accountability.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr style="height:27pt;">
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#E6E1EE" style="width:46.88%; border-bottom:solid 1pt #FFFFFF; border-left:solid 1pt #FFFFFF; border-right:solid 1pt #FFFFFF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Special Meeting of Shareholders. <font style="font-weight:normal;">By-Laws allow shareholders of record of at least 20% of the voting power of the outstanding stock to call a special meeting of shareholders.</font></p></td>
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#E6E1EE" style="width:53.12%; border-bottom:solid 1pt #FFFFFF; border-left:solid 1pt #FFFFFF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Further strengthens Board accountability and encourages engagement with substantial shareholders regarding important matters.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr style="height:27pt;">
<td valign="top"  style="width:46.88%; border-bottom:solid 1pt #FFFFFF; border-left:solid 1pt #FFFFFF; border-right:solid 1pt #FFFFFF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Proxy Access<font style="font-weight:normal;">. By-Laws provide for proxy access&#160;on market terms,&#160;enabling substantial shareholders to add their nominee(s) to the proxy </font><font style="font-weight:normal;color:#000000;">statement.</font></p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="width:53.12%; border-bottom:solid 1pt #FFFFFF; border-left:solid 1pt #FFFFFF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Further strengthens Board accountability and encourages engagement with substantial shareholders regarding Board composition.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr style="height:40.2pt;">
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#E6E1EE" style="width:46.88%; border-bottom:solid 1pt #FFFFFF; border-left:solid 1pt #FFFFFF; border-right:solid 1pt #FFFFFF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Regular Self-Assessment<font style="font-weight:normal;">. Regular Board, committee and director self-assessments include candid, one-on-one conversations between Governance Committee Chair and each director.</font></p></td>
<td valign="middle"  BGCOLOR="#E6E1EE" style="width:53.12%; border-bottom:solid 1pt #FFFFFF; border-left:solid 1pt #FFFFFF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:15.85pt;;text-indent:-13.7pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;<font style="color:#000000;font-family:Arial;">Promotes continuous process improvement at the Board and its committees.</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:15.85pt;;text-indent:-13.7pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;<font style="font-family:Arial;">Provides an opportunity </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:Arial;">to discuss individual directors&#8217; contributions and performance, as well as solicit views on improving Board and committee performance.</font></p></td>
</tr>
<tr style="height:53.4pt;">
<td valign="top"  style="width:46.88%; border-left:solid 1pt #FFFFFF; border-right:solid 1pt #FFFFFF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Tenure/Retirement<font style="font-weight:normal;">. Independent director tenure and retirement policies.</font></p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="width:53.12%; border-left:solid 1pt #FFFFFF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:15.85pt;;text-indent:-13.7pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;<font style="color:#000000;font-family:Arial;">Tenure/retirement policies promote ongoing evolution and refreshment.</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:15.85pt;;text-indent:-13.7pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;<font style="color:#000000;font-family:Arial;">Annual self-assessments provide a disciplined mechanism for director input into the Board&#8217;s evolution and succession planning process.</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:15.85pt;;text-indent:-13.7pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;<font style="color:#000000;font-family:Arial;">Average tenure for independent directors is approximately six years.</font></p></td>
</tr>
<tr style="height:53.4pt;">
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#E6E1EE" style="width:46.88%; border-left:solid 1pt #FFFFFF; border-right:solid 1pt #FFFFFF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Stock Ownership Requirements<font style="font-weight:normal;">. Directors must own shares of our Common Stock in an amount equal to five times the annual Board cash retainer within five years of joining the Board. Distribution of actual shares occurs six months after the director ends his or her service as a director.</font></p></td>
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#E6E1EE" style="width:53.12%; border-left:solid 1pt #FFFFFF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:15.85pt;;text-indent:-13.7pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;<font style="font-family:Arial;">Aligns directors&#8216; and shareholders&#8217; long-term interests; and</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:15.85pt;;text-indent:-13.7pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;<font style="font-family:Arial;">Many directors exceed the minimum requirement</font></p></td>
</tr>
<tr style="height:53.4pt;">
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" style="width:46.88%; border-bottom:solid 1pt #FFFFFF; border-left:solid 1pt #FFFFFF; border-right:solid 1pt #FFFFFF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Engagement with Shareholders. <font style="font-weight:normal;">We engage with shareholders to seek their input on emerging issues and to address their questions and concerns.</font></p></td>
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" style="width:53.12%; border-bottom:solid 1pt #FFFFFF; border-left:solid 1pt #FFFFFF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">During the past year, engaged with a diverse mix of shareholders representing approximately 55% of voting power on various topics including, among others, our leadership transition, executive compensation, strategy, capital allocation, business performance, corporate governance, sustainability and corporate social responsibility. These exchanges were candid and constructive.</p></td>
</tr>
</table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_Hlk530648499"></a><a name="_Hlk530648499"></a>&#160;</p>
<div>
