<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:1pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;color:#5A2D82;font-size:16pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU36"></a><a name="BOARD_COMMITTEES_MEMBERSHIP"></a><font style="color:#5A2D82;font-size:16pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="BOARD_COMMITTEES_MEMBERSHIP"></a>Board Committees</font><font style="color:#5A2D82;font-size:16pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> and Membership </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Governance Committee considers and makes recommendations to the Board regarding the Board&#8217;s committee structure and membership. </p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">The Board establishes its committee structure and designates the committee members and chairs following consideration of the Governance Committee&#8217;s recommendations. </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">The Board has adopted a written charter for each standing committee. The charters define each committee&#8217;s roles and responsibilities. </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">Independent directors comprise 100% of the Audit, Finance, Governance and Compensation Committees. </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">All committee chairs are independent. Committee chairs approve agendas and materials for their committee meetings. </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">Each committee meets regularly in executive session without management. </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">Committees may retain outside legal, financial and other advisors at the Company&#8217;s expense. </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Throughout 2018, the Board had, and it currently has, four standing committees: Audit, Finance, Governance and Compensation. The Board periodically reviews and rotates committee memberships. Accordingly, the membership shown in this table may change during 2019. </p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;color:#5A2D82;font-family:Arial;font-size:12pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="COMMITTEE_MEMBERSHIP1"></a><a name="COMMITTEE_MEMBERSHIP1"></a>Committee Membership</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<td valign="bottom"  BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0.75pt;padding-Top:0.75pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:37.88%; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&nbsp;</p></td>

<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:3.4%;text-indent:-3.4%;font-weight:bold;color:#5A2D82;font-family:Arial;font-size:12pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU37"></a><a name="MEETING_ATTENDANCE"></a><font style="font-weight:bold;color:#5A2D82;font-family:Arial;font-size:12pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="MEETING_ATTENDANCE"></a>Meeting At</font><font style="font-weight:bold;color:#5A2D82;font-family:Arial;font-size:12pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">tendance </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Directors are expected to attend all Board meetings, the Annual Meeting and all meetings of the committees on which they serve. We understand, however, that occasionally a director may be unable to attend a meeting, </p>

<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">The Board held eight meetings during 2018, and acted four times by unanimous written consent.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">During 2018, Mmes. Crew, Juliber and&#160;Rosenfeld (retired April 2018) and Messrs. Booth, Bunch, Ketchum, May, Neubauer, Peltz (resigned March 2018), Reynolds and Van de Put attended 100% of the meetings of the Board and all committees on which they served. Ms. Shi and Messrs. Mesquita, Siewert and van Boxmeer attended at least 77% of meetings of the Board and all committees on which they served. </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">

<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">11 of the 13 directors elected to the Board at the 2018 Annual Meeting of Shareholders attended that meeting. </p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;color:#5A2D82;font-family:Arial;font-size:12pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="AUDIT_COMMITTEE"></a><a name="AUDIT_COMMITTEE"></a>Audit Committee </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Board established the Audit Committee in accordance with Section&#160;3(a)(58)(A) of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934 (the &#8220;Exchange Act&#8221;). The Board has determined that all of the Audit Committee members are independent within the meaning of the Nasdaq listing standards and Rule 10A-3 of the Exchange Act. The Board also determined that all Audit Committee members are able to read and understand financial statements in accordance with Nasdaq listing standards and are financially literate in accordance with the New York Stock Exchange listing standards. The Board has determined that Fredric G. Reynolds and Patrick T. Siewert are <font style="font-style:italic;">&#8220;</font>audit committee financial experts&#8221; within the meaning of SEC regulations and have financial sophistication in accordance with Nasdaq listing standards. No Audit Committee member received any payments in 2018 from us other than compensation for service as a director. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Under its charter, the Audit Committee is responsible for overseeing our accounting and financial reporting processes and audits of our financial statements. The Audit Committee is directly responsible for the appointment, compensation, retention and oversight of our independent registered public accountants, including review of their qualifications, independence and performance. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Among other duties, the Audit Committee also oversees: </p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">

<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#5A2D82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#5A2D82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Audit Committee has established procedures for the receipt, retention and treatment, on a confidential basis, of any complaints we receive. We encourage employees and third-party individuals and organizations to report concerns about our accounting controls, auditing matters or anything else that appears to involve financial or other wrongdoing. To report such matters, please visit <font style="font-style:italic;text-decoration:underline;">www.mondelezinternational.com/about-us/compliance-and-integrity</font> for information about reporting options. </p>

<div>
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="center" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#E6E1EE" style="width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:12.25pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="toc498940_19"></a><a name="AUDIT_COMMITTEE_REPORT"></a><a name="AUDIT_COMMITTEE_REPORT"></a>Audit Committee Report for the Year Ended December&#160;31, 2018 </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:12.25pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Management has primary responsibility for Mondel&#275;z International&#8217;s financial statements and the reporting process, including the systems of internal control over financial reporting. Our role as the Audit Committee of the Mondel&#275;z International Board of Directors is to oversee Mondel&#275;z International&#8217;s accounting and financial reporting processes and audits of its financial statements. In addition, in 2018 we assisted the Board in its oversight of: </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:61.2pt;;text-indent:-18.35pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="font-size:9pt;color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font><font style="color:#000000;">Mondel&#275;z International&#8217;s compliance with legal and regulatory requirements; </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:61.2pt;;text-indent:-18.35pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="font-size:9pt;color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font><font style="color:#000000;">Mondel&#275;z International&#8217;s independent registered public accountants&#8217; qualifications, independence and performance; </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:61.2pt;;text-indent:-18.35pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="font-size:9pt;color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font><font style="color:#000000;">The performance of Mondel&#275;z International&#8217;s internal auditor and the internal audit function; and  </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:61.2pt;;text-indent:-18.35pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="font-size:9pt;color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font><font style="color:#000000;">Mondel&#275;z International&#8217;s risk assessment and risk management guidelines and policies. </font></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#E6E1EE" style="width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:12.2pt;;margin-right:2.22%;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Our duties include overseeing Mondel&#275;z International&#8217;s management, the internal audit department and PricewaterhouseCoopers LLP, Mondel&#275;z International&#8217;s independent registered public accountants, in their performance of the following functions, for which they are responsible: </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:12.25pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Management </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:61.2pt;;text-indent:-18.35pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="font-size:9pt;color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font><font style="color:#000000;">Preparing Mondel&#275;z International&#8217;s consolidated financial statements in accordance with accounting principles generally accepted in the United States of America (&#8220;U.S. GAAP&#8221;); </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:61.2pt;;text-indent:-18.35pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="font-size:9pt;color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font><font style="color:#000000;">Assessing and establishing effective financial reporting systems and internal controls and procedures; and </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:61.2pt;;text-indent:-18.35pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="font-size:9pt;color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font><font style="color:#000000;">Reporting on the effectiveness of Mondel&#275;z International&#8217;s internal control over financial reporting. </font></p></td>
</tr></table></div>

<td valign="middle"  style="width:94%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:16pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;color:#5A2D82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">2019 Proxy Statement</p></td>

<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#FCFCFC;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="Background-color:#5B2D83;">&#160;&#160;Board Committees and Membership&#160;&#160;</font></p>
<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<div>
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="center" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#E6E1EE" style="width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:12.25pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Internal Audit Department </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:61.2pt;;text-indent:-18.35pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="font-size:9pt;color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font><font style="color:#000000;">Assessing management&#8217;s system of internal controls and procedures; and </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:61.2pt;;text-indent:-18.35pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="font-size:9pt;color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font><font style="color:#000000;">Reporting on the effectiveness of that system. </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:12.25pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Independent Registered Public Accountants </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:61.2pt;;text-indent:-18.35pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="font-size:9pt;color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font><font style="color:#000000;">Auditing Mondel&#275;z International&#8217;s financial statements; </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:61.2pt;;text-indent:-18.35pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="font-size:9pt;color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font><font style="color:#000000;">Issuing an opinion about whether the financial statements conform with U.S. GAAP; and </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:61.2pt;;text-indent:-18.35pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="font-size:9pt;color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font><font style="color:#000000;">Annually auditing the effectiveness of Mondel&#275;z International&#8217;s internal control over financial reporting.</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:12.2pt;;margin-right:2.22%;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Periodically, we meet, both independently and collectively, with management, the internal auditor and/or the independent registered public accountants to, among other things: </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:61.2pt;;text-indent:-18.35pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="font-size:9pt;color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font><font style="color:#000000;">Discuss the quality of Mondel&#275;z International&#8217;s accounting and financial reporting processes and the adequacy and effectiveness of its internal controls and procedures; </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:61.2pt;;text-indent:-18.35pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="font-size:9pt;color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font><font style="color:#000000;">Review significant audit findings prepared by each of the independent registered public accountants and internal audit department, together with management&#8217;s responses; </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:61.2pt;;text-indent:-18.35pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="font-size:9pt;color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font><font style="color:#000000;">Review the overall scope and plans for the audits by the internal audit department and the independent registered public accountants; </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:61.2pt;;text-indent:-18.35pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="font-size:9pt;color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font><font style="color:#000000;">Review critical accounting policies and the significant estimates and judgments management used in preparing the financial statements and their appropriateness for Mondel&#275;z International&#8217;s business and current circumstances; and </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:61.2pt;;text-indent:-18.35pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="font-size:9pt;color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font><font style="color:#000000;">Review Mondel&#275;z International&#8217;s earnings releases. </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:12.2pt;;margin-right:2.22%;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">In addition to the activities outlined above, in 2018 we reviewed with management, among other things: </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:61.2pt;;text-indent:-18.35pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="font-size:9pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font>Guidelines and policies with respect to Mondel&#275;z International&#8217;s overall risk assessment and risk management; </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:61.2pt;;text-indent:-18.35pt;;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="font-size:9pt;color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font>Ongoing oversight of Mondel&#275;z International&#8217;s information technology and cybersecurity risk management and business continuity planning;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:61.2pt;;text-indent:-18.35pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="font-size:9pt;color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font><font style="color:#000000;">The U.S. and non-U.S. tax regulatory environment; and</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:61.2pt;;text-indent:-18.35pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="font-size:9pt;color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font><font style="color:#000000;">Data privacy and compliance with related rules and regulations. </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:12.2pt;;margin-right:2.22%;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU38"></a><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Prior to Mondel&#275;z International&#8217;s filing of its Annual Report on Form 10-K for the year ended December&#160;31, 2018 with the SEC, we also: </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:61.2pt;;text-indent:-18.35pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="font-size:9pt;color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font><font style="color:#000000;">Reviewed and discussed the audited financial statements with management and the independent registered public accountants; </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:61.2pt;;text-indent:-18.35pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="font-size:9pt;color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font><font style="color:#000000;">Discussed with the independent registered public accountants the items the independent registered public accountants are required to communicate to the Audit Committee in accordance with the applicable requirements of the Public Company Accounting Oversight Board; </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:61.2pt;;text-indent:-18.35pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="font-size:9pt;color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font><font style="color:#000000;">Received from the independent registered public accountants the written disclosures and the letter required by applicable requirements of the Public Company Accounting Oversight Board regarding the independent registered public accountants&#8217; communications with us concerning independence; and </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:61.2pt;;text-indent:-18.35pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="font-size:9pt;color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font><font style="color:#000000;">Discussed with the independent registered public accountants their independence from Mondel&#275;z International, including reviewing non-audit services and fees to assure compliance with (i)&#160;regulations prohibiting the independent registered public accountants from performing specified services that could impair their independence, and (ii)&#160;Mondel&#275;z International&#8217;s and the Audit Committee&#8217;s policies. </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:12.2pt;;margin-right:2.22%;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Based upon the review and discussions described in this report and without other independent verification, and subject to the limitations of our role and responsibilities outlined in this report and in our written charter, we recommended to the Board, and the Board approved, that the audited consolidated financial statements be included in Mondel&#275;z International&#8217;s Annual Report on Form 10-K for the year ended December&#160;31, 2018, which was filed with the SEC on February&#160;8, 2019. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;margin-left:12.2pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Audit Committee: </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:12.2pt;;margin-right:2.22%;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Fredric G. Reynolds, Chair</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:12.2pt;;margin-right:2.22%;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Debra A. Crew </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:12.2pt;;margin-right:2.22%;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Jorge S. Mesquita </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:12.2pt;;margin-right:2.22%;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Christiana S. Shi </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:12.2pt;;margin-right:2.22%;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Patrick T. Siewert </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:4pt;margin-left:12.25pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:2pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
</tr>
</table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU39"></a><a name="PREAPPROVAL_POLICIES"></a><a name="PREAPPROVAL_POLICIES"></a>Pre-Approval Policies </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Audit Committee&#8217;s policy is to pre-approve all audit and non-audit services provided by the independent registered public accountants. These services may include audit services, audit-related services, tax services and other permissible non-audit services. The pre-approval authority details the particular service or category of service that the independent registered public accountants will perform. Management reports to the Audit Committee on the actual fees charged by the independent registered public accountants for each category of service. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">During the year, circumstances may arise when it becomes necessary to engage the independent registered public accountants for additional services not contemplated in the original pre-approval authority. In those instances, the committee approves the services before we engage the independent registered public accountants. In case approval is needed before a scheduled committee meeting, the committee has delegated pre-approval authority to its Chair. The Chair must report on such pre-approval decisions at the committee&#8217;s next regular meeting. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Audit Committee pre-approved all 2018 audit and non-audit services provided by the independent registered public accountants. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="INDEPENDENT_REGISTERED_PUBLIC_ACCOUNTANT"></a><a name="INDEPENDENT_REGISTERED_PUBLIC_ACCOUNTANT"></a>Independent Registered Public Accountants&#8217; Fees </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Aggregate fees for professional services rendered by our independent registered public accountants, PricewaterhouseCoopers LLP, for 2018 and 2017 were: </p>

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:1pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;color:#FCFCFC;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="Background-color:#5B2D83;">&#160;&#160;Board Committees and Membership&#160;&#160;</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU40"></a><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Audit Fees include (a)&#160;the integrated audit of our consolidated financial statements, including statutory audits of the financial statements of our affiliates and our internal control over financial reporting and (b)&#160;the reviews of our unaudited condensed consolidated interim financial statements (quarterly financial statements). </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Audit-Related Fees include professional services in connection with employee benefit plan audits and procedures related to various other audit and special reports. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Tax Fees include professional services in connection with tax compliance and advice. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">All Other Fees include professional services in connection with seminars and compliance reviews. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">All fees above include out-of-pocket expenses. </p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;color:#5A2D82;font-family:Arial;font-size:12pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="FINANCE_COMMITTEE"></a><a name="FINANCE_COMMITTEE"></a>Finance Committee </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Board has determined that all of the Finance Committee members are independent within the meaning of the Nasdaq listing standards. The Finance Committee&#8217;s charter sets out its responsibilities, which include reviewing and making recommendations to the Board on significant financial matters, including: </p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">at least annually, the Company&#8217;s long-term capital structure, including financing plans, projected financial structure, funding requirements, target credit ratings and return on invested capital; </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">

<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">

<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">

<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">Board authorization and delegation levels with respect to financing matters. </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Finance Committee also reviews and discusses with management: </p>
<div align="left">

<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">

<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">results of transactions such as acquisitions, divestitures, joint ventures and investments in excess of $100&#160;million; and </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">

<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">the cash-flow impact of non-debt obligations including funding pension and other post-retirement benefit plans. </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;line-height:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;color:#5A2D82;font-family:Arial;font-size:12pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="GOVERNANCE_MEMBERSHIP_PUBLIC_AFFAIRS_COM"></a><a name="GOVERNANCE_MEMBERSHIP_PUBLIC_AFFAIRS_COM"></a>Governance, Membership and Public Affairs Committee </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Board has determined that all of the Governance Committee members are independent within the meaning of the Nasdaq listing standards. The Governance Committee&#8217;s charter sets out its responsibilities. Among its responsibilities are: </p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">

<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">

<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU41"></a><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"></font><font style="color:#000000;">oversee policies and programs related to corporate citizenship, social responsibility and public policy issues significant to Mondel&#275;z International such as sustainability and environmental responsibility; food labeling, marketing and packaging; and philanthropic and political activities and contributions; and </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:8%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">monitor issues, trends, internal and external factors and relationships that may affect Mondel&#275;z International&#8217;s public image and reputation. </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-top:18pt;line-height:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="POLITICAL_ACTIVITY_GOVERNANCE"></a><a name="POLITICAL_ACTIVITY_GOVERNANCE"></a>Political Activity and Governance</p>
<p style="margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We maintain a robust governance framework for overseeing our political activities. We do so responsibly and transparently, with priority on compliance with federal, state and local laws. The Governance Committee oversees our policies and programs related to corporate citizenship and public policy issues significant to the Company. As our success depends on sound public policies, we regularly work with government officials regarding matters of concern in accordance with applicable laws and regulations. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Mondel&#275;z International has proud history of involvement in the communities where employees live and work, including participation in the political process to support policies that impact our communities, employees and businesses. We provide comprehensive disclosure of political activity through our website (<font style="text-decoration:none;color:#000000;">www.mondelezinternational.com/investors/corporate-governance/board-responsibilities-leadership/board-oversight</font>) reflecting our policies and procedures for making political contributions and expenditures. In addition, the website provides information on our lobbying activities and a link to the lobbying disclosure reports we file with the U.<font style="color:#000000;">S. Congress. A list of trade associations to which we pay dues of over $50,000 annually, including the portion of dues attributable to lobbying, can also be found on our website. As demonstrated by the robustness of our reporting, we are firmly committed to providing shareholders with transparency over our political activities.</font></p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;line-height:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;color:#5A2D82;font-family:Arial;font-size:12pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="HUMAN_RESOURCES_COMPENSATION_COMMITTEE"></a><a name="HUMAN_RESOURCES_COMPENSATION_COMMITTEE"></a>Human Resources and Compensation Committee </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="HUMAN_RESOURCES_COMPENSATION_COMMITTEE_I"></a><a name="HUMAN_RESOURCES_COMPENSATION_COMMITTEE_I"></a>Human Resources and Compensation Committee Independence, Interlocks and Insider Participation </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Board determined that all Compensation Committee members are independent within the meaning of the Nasdaq listing standards, including the heightened independence criteria for Compensation Committee members. All are &#8220;non-employee&#8221; directors under SEC rules and outsider directors under the Internal Revenue Code of 1986, as amended (the &#8220;Code&#8221;). None of the Compensation Committee&#8217;s members are or were: </p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">an officer or employee of Mondel&#275;z International; </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">

<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">

<td valign="top">

<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">

<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">

<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">

<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">an executive officer of another entity at which one of our executive officers serves on the board of directors or the Compensation Committee. </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;line-height:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="RESPONSIBILITIES"></a><a name="RESPONSIBILITIES"></a>Responsibilities </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Compensation Committee&#8217;s charter sets out its responsibilities. Among its responsibilities are to: </p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">

<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">establish our executive compensation philosophy; </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">determine the group of companies the Compensation Committee uses to benchmark executive and director compensation; </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>

<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">

<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">assess the independence of the Compensation Committee&#8217;s outside advisors and at least annually assess whether the work of its compensation consultants has raised any conflict of interest that must be disclosed in our annual report and Proxy Statement. </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Compensation Committee has the authority to delegate any of its responsibilities to the committee&#8217;s Chair, another Compensation Committee member or a subcommittee of Compensation Committee members, unless prohibited by law, regulation or any Nasdaq listing standard. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;line-height:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="COMPENSATION_COMMITTEES_USE_AN_INDEPENDE"></a><a name="COMPENSATION_COMMITTEES_USE_AN_INDEPENDE"></a>The Compensation Committee&#8217;s Use of an Independent Compensation Consultant </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Compensation Committee retains an independent compensation consultant to assist in evaluating executive compensation programs and advise regarding the amount and form of executive and director compensation. It uses a consultant to provide additional assurance that our executive and director compensation programs are reasonable, competitive and consistent with our objectives. It directly engages the consultant under an engagement letter that the Compensation Committee reviews at least annually. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Since September 2009, the Compensation Committee has retained Compensation Advisory Partners LLC (&#8220;CAP&#8221;) as its independent compensation consultant. Annually, the Compensation Committee reviews CAP&#8217;s engagement. During 2018, CAP provided the Compensation Committee advice and services, including: </p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">regularly participating in Compensation Committee meetings including executive sessions that exclude management; </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">consulting with the Compensation Committee Chair and being available to consult with other Committee members between committee meetings; </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">providing competitive peer group compensation data for executive positions and evaluating how the compensation we pay the NEOs (as described under &#8220;Compensation Discussion and Analysis&#8221;) relates both to the Company&#8217;s performance and to how the peers compensate their executives; </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">analyzing &#8220;best practices&#8221; and providing advice about design of the annual and long-term incentive plans, including selecting performance metrics; </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">advising on the composition of the Compensation Survey Peer Group and the Performance Peer Group (as described in the &#8220;Compensation Discussion and Analysis&#8221;) that we use for benchmarking pay and performance; </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div>
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="center" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top"  style="width:6%;">
<p style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="width:94%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
