<td valign="middle"  BGCOLOR="#683F8B" style="padding-Right:4pt;width:6%;">
<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:2pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#FFFFFF;font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">32</a></p></td>
<td valign="middle"  style="width:94%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:16pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;color:#5A2D82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">2019 Proxy Statement</p></td>
</tr>
</table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:1pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;color:#FCFCFC;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="Background-color:#5B2D83;">&#160;&#160;Board Committees and Membership&#160;&#160;</font></p>
<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU43"></a><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"></font><font style="color:#000000;">updating the Compensation Committee on executive compensation trends, issues and regulatory developments; and</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">assessing and recommending non-employee director compensation. </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">For the year ended December&#160;31, 2018, CAP provided no services to Mondel&#275;z International other than consulting services to the Compensation Committee regarding executive and non-employee director compensation. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">At least annually, the Compensation Committee reviews the current engagements and the objectivity and independence of the advice that CAP provides to it on executive and non-employee director compensation. The Compensation Committee considered the six specific independence factors adopted by the SEC and Nasdaq and determined that CAP is independent and CAP&#8217;s work did not raise any conflicts of interest. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;line-height:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="EXECUTIVE_FICERS_HAVE_A_LIMITED_ROLE_IN_"></a><a name="EXECUTIVE_FICERS_HAVE_A_LIMITED_ROLE_IN_"></a>Executive Officers Have a Limited Role in the Compensation Committee&#8217;s Determination of Executive Compensation and Recommendations to the Board Regarding Non-Employee Director Compensation </p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">Each year, the CEO presents compensation recommendations for CEO direct reports and the other executive officers, including the NEOs. The Compensation Committee reviews and discusses these recommendations with the CEO but retains full discretion over the compensation of these employees. </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">The CEO does not make recommendations or participate in deliberations regarding the CEO&#8217;s own compensation. </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">Executive officers do not play a role in determining or recommending the amount or form of non-employee director compensation. </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-top:8pt;line-height:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="COMPENSATION_COMMITTEES_ROLE_IN_MANAGEME"></a><a name="COMPENSATION_COMMITTEES_ROLE_IN_MANAGEME"></a>The Compensation Committee&#8217;s Role in Management Succession Planning and Development </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="line-height:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Succession planning for senior management positions, which facilitates continuity of leadership over the long-term, is critical to our success and important at all levels within our organization. Our Board&#8217;s involvement in leadership development and succession planning is systematic, strategic and continuous. The Compensation Committee oversees the development and retention of senior management talent while also maintaining an appropriate succession plan for our CEO. Additionally, <font style="color:#000000;">the Board has contingency plans for emergencies such as the death or disability of the CEO. </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Compensation Committee, together with the CEO, regularly reviews senior management talent, including readiness to take on additional leadership roles and developmental opportunities needed to prepare leaders for greater responsibilities. The CEO also provides a regular review to the Compensation Committee of the executive leadership team. While the Compensation Committee has the primary responsibility to develop succession plans for the CEO position, it annually reports to the Board and decisions are made at the Board level. Potential leaders interact with Board members through formal presentations and during informal events.<font style="color:#000000;"> </font>More broadly, the Board is updated on key talent indicators for the overall workforce, including diversity, recruiting and development programs. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;line-height:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:8pt;line-height:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="HOW_COMPENSATION_COMMITTEE_MANAGES_COMPE"></a><a name="HOW_COMPENSATION_COMMITTEE_MANAGES_COMPE"></a>How the Compensation Committee Manages Compensation-Related Risk </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">As it does each year, in 2018, the Compensation Committee evaluated whether our compensation designs, policies and practices operate to discourage our executive officers and other employees from taking unnecessary or excessive risks. As described in the &#8220;Compensation Discussion and Analysis,&#8221; we design our compensation to incentivize executives and other employees to achieve the Company&#8217;s financial and strategic goals as well as individual performance goals that promote long-term shareholder returns. Our compensation design discourages our executives and other employees from taking excessive risks for short-term benefits that may harm the Company and our shareholders in the long-term. The Compensation Committee uses various strategies to mitigate risk, including: </p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">using both short-term and long-term performance-based compensation so that executives do not focus solely on short-term performance; </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">weighting executive compensation heavily toward long-term incentives to encourage sustainable shareholder value and accountability for long-term results; </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">using multiple relevant performance measures in our incentive plan designs so executives do not place undue importance on one measure, which could distort the results that we want to incent; </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div>
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="center" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top"  style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0pt;padding-Top:0pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:94%;">
<p style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0pt;padding-Top:0pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:6%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td valign="middle"  style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0pt;padding-Top:0pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:94%;">
<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;margin-right:2.96%;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:16pt;font-family:Calibri;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><img src="gycirsmwh4vw000013.jpg" title="" alt="" style="width:85px;height:20px;"></p></td>
<td valign="middle"  BGCOLOR="#683F8B" style="padding-left:4pt;padding-Right:0pt;padding-Top:0pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:6%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:2pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#FFFFFF;font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">33</a></p></td>
</tr>
</table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:1pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;color:#FCFCFC;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="Background-color:#5B2D83;">&#160;&#160;Board Committees and Membership&#160;&#160;</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU44"></a><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"></font><font style="color:#000000;">weighting business and individual performance in our annual cash incentive program so that executives and employees do not have too narrow a focus; </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">capping the amount of incentives that may be awarded or granted; </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">retaining discretion to reduce incentive awards based on unforeseen or unintended consequences and clawback compensation in specified circumstances; </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">requiring our top executives to hold a significant amount of their compensation in Common Stock and prohibiting them from hedging, pledging or engaging in short sales of their Common Stock; </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">minimizing use of employment contracts; </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">not backdating or re-pricing option grants; and </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">not paying severance benefits on change in control events unless the affected executive is first involuntarily terminated without cause or terminates due to good reason. </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">In addition, the Audit Committee oversees our ethics and compliance programs that educate executives and other employees on appropriate behavior and the consequences of inappropriate actions. These programs not only drive compliance and integrity but also encourage employees with knowledge of bad behavior to report concerns by providing multiple reporting avenues while protecting reporting employees against retaliation. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">CAP also reviewed the Compensation Committee&#8217;s risk analysis, including the underlying procedures, and confirmed the Compensation Committee&#8217;s conclusion below. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">In light of these analyses, the Compensation Committee believes that our compensation programs do not create risks that are reasonably likely to have a material adverse effect on the Company. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-top:8pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-right:6.67%;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="GOVERNANCE_FRAMEWORK_AROUND_USE_EPS_IN_O"></a><a name="GOVERNANCE_FRAMEWORK_AROUND_USE_EPS_IN_O"></a>Governance Framework Around the Use of EPS in Our Incentive Programs </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-right:6.67%;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-right:6.67%;text-indent:0%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Compensation Committee believes it is appropriate to base executive compensation on performance metrics that align with our external reporting framework and how shareholders and other stakeholders measure our performance.&#160;Accordingly, the EPS metric we use in our incentive programs, like our external targets, accounts for our capital allocation plans for the year, including expected share repurchases.&#160;The Compensation Committee recognizes there are differing views among investors as to whether share repurchases should be factored into EPS targets in executive compensation programs, but believes our robust governance and compensation practices mitigate the risk that an executive would act imprudently. Specifically, </p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:8.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;"></font><font style="color:#000000;">the Compensation Committee establishes the performance metrics and targets for both the annual and long-term incentive programs;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:6.67%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:8.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;"></font><font style="color:#000000;">the Board oversees our capital allocation process and reviews a budget each year for capital deployment, including share repurchases with the goal of balancing investment in growth and returning cash to shareholders (as demonstrated through our historical investments in capital expenditures and research and development); and</font></p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:6.67%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:8.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;"></font><font style="color:#000000;">the Compensation Committee designs both the annual and long-term incentive programs so there is a mix of performance metrics such that even if executives were able to deploy an excessive amount of cash towards share repurchases to maximize EPS, there would be offsetting impacts on other performance metrics, with no clear visibility towards increasing payouts.</font></p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:6.67%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:1pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<div>
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="center" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top"  style="width:6%;">
<p style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="width:94%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td valign="middle"  BGCOLOR="#683F8B" style="padding-Right:4pt;width:6%;">
<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:2pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#FFFFFF;font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">34</a></p></td>
<td valign="middle"  style="width:94%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:16pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;color:#5A2D82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">2019 Proxy Statement</p></td>
</tr>
</table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:1pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;color:#5A2D82;font-size:16pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU45"></a><a name="COMPENSATION_NONEMPLOYEE_DIRECTORS"></a><font style="color:#5A2D82;font-size:16pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="COMPENSATION_NONEMPLOYEE_DIRECTORS"></a>Compensation of Non-</font><font style="color:#5A2D82;font-size:16pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Employee Directors </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Review of Non-Employee Director Compensation </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Our Compensation Committee reviews non-employee director compensation to confirm the compensation we offer is market appropriate without being excessive. To support the Compensation Committee&#8217;s review, as requested, CAP: </p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:6.6%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">benchmarks our non-employee director compensation against our Compensation Survey Peer Group and other Fortune 100 companies; </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:6.6%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">assesses the form and amount of our non-employee director compensation; and </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:6.6%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">provides the Compensation Committee with this data and an independent assessment of the appropriateness and competitiveness of our non-employee director compensation. </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Using CAP&#8217;s assessment, the Compensation Committee determines whether to recommend the Board make any changes to the compensation for the non-employee directors. No changes were made to non-employee director compensation for 2018. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Summary of 2018 Compensation Elements</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<div>
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="center" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="bottom"  BGCOLOR="#683F8B" style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0.75pt;padding-Top:0.75pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:79.88%; border-top:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-left:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-right:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">

</table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We do not pay non-employee directors any meeting fees. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We also do not pay a Company employee who serves as a director any additional compensation for serving as a director. Currently, <font style="color:#000000;">Dirk Van de Put </font>is the only director who is a Company employee. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:8pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Plan Limits on Non-Employee Director Grants </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Our shareholder-approved Amended and Restated 2005 Performance Incentive Plan (the &#8220;Equity Plan&#8221;) caps the maximum fair market value of Common Stock grants made to any non-employee director in any calendar year at $500,000. All stock grants made in 2018 to non-employee directors were significantly below this amount. See the &#8220;2018 Non-Employee Director Compensation&#8221; and &#8220;2018 Non-Employee Director Equity Awards&#8221; tables for specific values. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Cash Compensation&#160;&#8211;&#160;Board, Lead Director and Committee Chair Retainers </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We pay our non-employee directors their cash retainers quarterly. The Mondel&#275;z International, Inc. 2001 Compensation Plan for Non-Employee Directors allows directors to defer 25%, 50%, 75% or 100% of their cash retainers into notional unfunded accounts. These accounts mirror certain of the investment options under the Thrift 401(k) Plan offered to U.S. salaried employees. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">If the Board appoints a non-employee director during the year (i.e., other than at the annual meeting of shareholders), we pay that director prorated compensation for the balance of the year. We prorate cash compensation based on the number of days remaining in the calendar year. </p>
<p style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:1pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<div>
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="center" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top"  style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0pt;padding-Top:0pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:94%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0pt;padding-Top:0pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:6%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td valign="middle"  style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0pt;padding-Top:0pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:94%;">
<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;margin-right:2.96%;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:16pt;font-family:Calibri;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><img src="gycirsmwh4vw000013.jpg" title="" alt="" style="width:85px;height:20px;"></p></td>
<td valign="middle"  BGCOLOR="#683F8B" style="padding-left:4pt;padding-Right:0pt;padding-Top:0pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:6%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:2pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#FFFFFF;font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">35</a></p></td>
</tr>
</table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:1pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;color:#FCFCFC;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="Background-color:#5B2B82;">&#160;&#160;</font><font style="Background-color:#5B2D83;">Compensation of Non-Employee Directors&#160;</font><font style="Background-color:#5B2B82;">&#160;</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU46"></a><font style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Equity Compensation</font><font style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#160;&#8211;&#160;</font><font style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Annual Equity Grant </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We make annual equity grants to our non-employee directors following the annual meeting of shareholders. In order to align directors&#8217; interests with shareholders during the directors&#8217; service, grants are in the form of vested deferred stock units. We distribute actual shares six months after the director ends his or her service as a director. When we pay a dividend on our Common Stock, we accrue the value of the dividends that we would have paid on the deferred stock units. Six months after the director ends his or her service as a director, we issue shares to the director equal to the accumulated accrued value. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">If the Board appoints a non-employee director during the year (i.e., other than at the annual meeting of shareholders), we prorate the annual equity grant value based on the number of months until the next annual meeting of shareholders over a denominator of twelve months. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Director Stock Ownership Guidelines </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">To align our non-employee directors&#8217; and our shareholders&#8217; interests, we expect our non-employee directors to hold shares of our Common Stock. Our expectations are as follows: </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr style="height:17.9pt;">
<td valign="middle"  style="width:24.44%; border-bottom:solid 1pt #5B2B82;">
<p style="margin-bottom:1pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:5.85pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#5A2D82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Key Provisions</p></td>
<td valign="middle"  style="padding-left:7.2pt;padding-Right:0pt;padding-Top:0pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:75.56%; border-bottom:solid 1pt #5B2B82;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#5A2D82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Explanation of Key Provisions</p></td>
</tr>
<tr style="height:18.45pt;">
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#E6E1EE" style="width:24.44%; border-top:solid 1pt #5B2B82;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:2pt;margin-left:5.85pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Ownership Expectation</p></td>
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#E6E1EE" style="width:75.56%; border-top:solid 1pt #5B2B82;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:2pt;margin-left:23.95pt;;text-indent:-15.3pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Amount equal to five times the annual Board cash retainer (i.e., $550,000).</p></td>
</tr>
<tr style="height:18.1pt;">
<td valign="top"  style="width:24.44%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:2pt;margin-left:5.85pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Time to Meet Expectation</p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="width:75.56%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:2pt;margin-left:23.95pt;;text-indent:-15.3pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Five years from joining the Board as a director.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr style="height:31.6pt;">
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#E6E1EE" style="width:24.44%;">
<p style="margin-top:2pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:5.85pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Shares Counted Toward Ownership</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:5.85pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;;font-size:8pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#E6E1EE" style="width:75.56%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:2pt;margin-left:9pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Common Stock, including sole ownership, deferred stock units and accounts over which the director has direct or indirect ownership or control.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr style="height:47.35pt;">
<td valign="top"  style="width:24.44%; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">
<p style="margin-top:2pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:5.75pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Holding&#160;Expectation</p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="width:75.56%; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:2pt;margin-left:8.65pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Company does not release the shares underlying the deferred stock units until six months after the director ends his or her service as a director. The Company does not require that shares be held after distribution/issuance.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:2pt;margin-left:8.65pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:1pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
</tr>
</table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">If a non-employee director does not meet these ownership expectations, the Lead Director will consider the non-employee director&#8217;s particular situation and may take action as deemed appropriate. As of <font style="color:#000000;">March 12, 2019, each </font>director serving for at least five years met or exceeded the ownership expectation. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Company Match for Director Charitable Contributions </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Non-employee directors are eligible to participate in the Mondel&#275;z International Foundation (the &#8220;Foundation&#8221;) Matching Gift Program. Each year, the Foundation will generally match up to $15,000 in contributions by a non-employee director to any 501(c)(3) non-profit organization(s). </p>

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(1) Includes all retainer fees earned or deferred pursuant to the 2001 Compensation Plan for Non-Employee Directors. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(2) The amounts shown in this column represent the full grant date fair value of the deferred stock unit grants in 2018 as computed in accordance with Financial Accounting Standards Board (&#8220;FASB&#8221;) Accounting Standards Codification (&#8220;ASC&#8221;) Topic 718. Assumptions used in the calculation of these amounts are included in Note 11 to the consolidated financial statements contained in our 2018 Form 10-K. The deferred stock units are immediately vested, but receipt of the shares is deferred until six months after the director no longer serves on the Board. The 2018 Non-Employee Director Equity Awards Table provides further detail on the non-employee director grants made in 2018 and the number of stock awards outstanding as of December&#160;31, 2018. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(3) Represents Foundation contributions made as part of the Foundation Matching Gift Program. Annual match limits are based on gift date, not the match date by the Foundation. As such, the amounts reflected may represent gifts that directors made in 2017 but the Foundation did not match until 2018. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(4) In accordance with our policy, Ms. Crew and Mr. May each received two deferred stock unit grants in 2018. In connection with their respective appointments as directors effective March 1, 2018, they each received a prorated deferred stock unit grant of 1,003 units. In addition, each received the annual deferred stock unit grant of 4,429 units on May 16, 2018 simultaneously with all of the other non-employee directors in connection with the 2018 annual meeting of shareholders.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(5) Effective March 1, 2018, Mr. Peltz concluded his service on the Board. His 2018 retainer payment was prorated based on the date his term ended. He did not receive an annual equity grant during 2018.</p>

<td valign="bottom"  BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0.75pt;padding-Top:0.75pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:44.92%; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #BFC5BF; border-left:solid 0.75pt #BFC5BF; border-right:solid 0.75pt #BFC5BF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:6.85pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#000000;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">van Boxmeer, Jean-Fran&#231;ois</p></td>
<td valign="bottom"  BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0.75pt;padding-Top:0.75pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:18.34%; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #BFC5BF; border-left:solid 0.75pt #BFC5BF; border-right:solid 0.75pt #BFC5BF;">
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#000000;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">4,429</p></td>
<td valign="bottom"  BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0.75pt;padding-Top:0.75pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:18.34%; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #BFC5BF; border-left:solid 0.75pt #BFC5BF; border-right:solid 0.75pt #BFC5BF;">
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#000000;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">175,034</p></td>

<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#000000;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">35,120</p></td>

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(1) The amounts shown in this column represent the full grant date fair value of the deferred stock units granted in 2018 as computed in accordance with FASB ASC Topic 718.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(2) In accordance with our policy, Ms. Crew and Mr. May each received two deferred stock unit grants in 2018. In connection with their respective appointments as directors effective March 1, 2018, they each received a prorated deferred stock unit grant of 1,003 units. In addition, each received the annual deferred stock unit grant of 4,429 units on May 16, 2018 simultaneously with all of the other non-employee directors in connection with the 2018 annual meeting of shareholders.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:4pt;margin-left:3.4%;text-indent:-3.4%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:8pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<td valign="middle"  style="width:94%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:16pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;color:#5A2D82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">2019 Proxy Statement</p></td>

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:1pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;color:#5B2B82;font-size:16pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU49"></a><a name="COMPENSATION_DISCUSSION_ANALYSIS"></a><font style="color:#5B2B82;font-size:16pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="COMPENSATION_DISCUSSION_ANALYSIS"></a>Compensation Discus</font><font style="color:#5B2B82;font-size:16pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">sion and Analysis </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;;font-size:6pt;"><a name="OVERVIEW"></a>&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We delivered key financial and strategic commitments in 2018: </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">Net revenues increased 0.2%; Organic Net Revenue</font><sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(1)</sup>&#160;<font style="color:#000000;">grew 2.4%; </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">Gross profit grew&#160;$318 million&#160;(+3%); Adjusted </font>Gross Profit<sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(1)</sup> grew&#160;$352 million (+4%) on a constant currency basis; </p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">Diluted EPS was $2.28, up 23%; Adjusted EPS<sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(1)</sup> was $2.43, up 15% on a constant-currency basis; and</p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">Cash provided by operating activities was $3.9 billion; Free Cash Flow<sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(1)</sup> was $2.9 billion.</p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We announced an 18% dividend per share increase in the third quarter of 2018 and returned $3.4&#160;billion of capital to shareholders while continuing to invest in our business. <font style="color:#000000;">We believe the compensation paid to our named executive officers for 2018 appropriately reflects and rewards their contribution to our performance. </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Our results demonstrate the power of our brands, the strength of our global footprint and the potential of our strategic plan. In September 2018, <font style="color:#000000;">we unveiled our new strategy to position us to lead the snacking industry. Our new strategy has three key pillars centered around:&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">Accelerating consumer-centric growth;</p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">Driving operational excellence; and</p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">Building a winning growth culture.</p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">To accelerate our top line, we are emphasizing volume-driven growth and more agile innovation. In addition, we are increasing investment across both local and global brands, as well as pursuing opportunities to expand into faster growing channels and geographies. Our new strategy also includes a focus on operational excellence across the entire organization. We intend to drive end-to-end improvements in our processes and systems to make us more efficient. We are building a winning growth culture with a &#8220;local first&#8221; commercial approach that emphasizes speed, innovation and sustainable growth and profitability metrics that are aligned with our overall financial goals, which we believe will generate attractive long-term returns. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">To drive our goals, we will focus on changing our ways of working, which includes shifting more decision making down to a local level, reducing complexity, increasing our test and learn approach to innovation and creating a reward structure that is fully aligned with our growth objectives. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">To align our reward structure with our new strategy, our 2019 compensation program will emphasize Organic Volume (sales volume that excludes the impact of acquisitions and divestitures) and Organic Net Revenue Growth, Adjusted Gross Profit and Adjusted Operating Income (&#8220;OI&#8221;) dollar growth (or Adjusted EPS for Corporate) at planned foreign exchange rates and Free Cash Flow. We will shift focus from Adjusted Gross Margin Percent to Adjusted Gross Profit dollars and increase investments to drive growth. As we are targeting high single-digit Adjusted EPS growth over the long term, Adjusted OI dollar growth will be an important measure. To incent a high quality of results, market share will return as an overlay in the Annual Incentive Program. See &#8220;Changes to our Executive Compensation Program&#8221; for more specific detail on the changes made to support our new strategy.</p>
<p style="Background-color:#FFFFFF;margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">This Compensation Discussion and Analysis explains the guiding principles and practices upon which our executive compensation program is based as well as the compensation paid to our 2018 named executive officers:</p>
<p style="Background-color:#FFFFFF;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;">&nbsp;</p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:101.66%;">

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:3.6pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:1pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#160;</p></td>

<p style="margin-top:1pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:7.15pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Executive Vice President and President, North America</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:3.6pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:1pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#160;</p></td>

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:0%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(1)</sup></font><font style="font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> See definition and </font><font style="font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">GAAP to non-GAAP reconciliation in Annex A</font><font style="font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">. </font></p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"></p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:1pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<div>
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="center" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top"  style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0pt;padding-Top:0pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:94%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0pt;padding-Top:0pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:6%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
