<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">Multiple lines of business. </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:20%;"><tr><td style="width:20%;"></td></tr><tr><td valign="top"  style="border-bottom:Solid 1pt #000000;"><p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:0pt;font-size:8pt;">&nbsp;</p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(1)</sup></font><font style="font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> </font><font style="font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">For foreign-based competitors, the Compensation Committee will continue to monitor pay practices as available and relevant. </font></p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:96.6%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"></p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;">&nbsp;</p>
<div>
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="center" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top"  style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0pt;padding-Top:0pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:94%;">
<p style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0pt;padding-Top:0pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:6%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td valign="middle"  style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0pt;padding-Top:0pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:94%;">
<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;margin-right:2.96%;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:16pt;font-family:Calibri;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><img src="gycirsmwh4vw000013.jpg" title="" alt="" style="width:85px;height:20px;"></p></td>
<td valign="middle"  BGCOLOR="#683F8B" style="padding-left:4pt;padding-Right:0pt;padding-Top:0pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:6%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:2pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#FFFFFF;font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">43</a></p></td>
</tr>
</table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:1pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;color:#FCFCFC;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="Background-color:#5B2D83;">&#160;&#160;Compensation Discussion and Analysis&#160;&#160;</font></p>
<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU53"></a><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The companies added to the Compensation Survey Peer Group are U.S.-based consumer product companies that are of similar complexity and size and have sizable foreign operations. Companies removed from the Compensation Survey Peer Group included both foreign-based competitors where benchmark compensation data is unavailable for most roles and U.S.-based companies that are more complex or in market sectors that are irrelevant to our Company. </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Compensation Committee, with input from its independent compensation consultant, CAP, also reviewed the Performance Peer Group but did not make any changes as that group continues to be a good fit for performance comparisons. See &#8220;Peer Groups for Pay and Performance&#8221; for additional information on our peer groups.</p>
<div>
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="center" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top"  style="width:6%;">
<p style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="width:94%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td valign="middle"  BGCOLOR="#683F8B" style="padding-Right:4pt;width:6%;">
<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:2pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#FFFFFF;font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">44</a></p></td>
<td valign="middle"  style="width:94%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:16pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;color:#5A2D82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">2019 Proxy Statement</p></td>
</tr>
</table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:1pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;color:#FCFCFC;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="Background-color:#5B2D83;">&#160;&#160;Compensation Discussion and Analysis&#160;&#160;</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;color:#5A2D82;font-family:Arial;font-size:12pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU54"></a><a name="OUR_EXECUTIVE_COMPENSATION_GOVERNANCE_PR"></a><font style="font-weight:bold;color:#5A2D82;font-family:Arial;font-size:12pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="OUR_EXECUTIVE_COMPENSATION_GOVERNANCE_PR"></a>Our Executive Compensati</font><font style="font-weight:bold;color:#5A2D82;font-family:Arial;font-size:12pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">on Governance Practices</font></p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;color:#5A2D82;font-family:Arial;font-size:12pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Reflect Best Practices to Protect and Promote our Shareholders&#8217; Interests</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<div>
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="center" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="middle"  BGCOLOR="#683F8B" style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0pt;padding-Top:0pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:50%; border-top:solid 0.75pt #5B2B82; border-left:solid 0.75pt #5B2B82; border-right:solid 0.75pt #5B2B82;">
<p style="margin-bottom:3pt;margin-top:3pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;color:#FFFFFF;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#160;&#160;&#160;What we do:<font style="font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;color:#000000;">&#160;</font></p></td>
<td valign="middle"  BGCOLOR="#683F8B" style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:2pt;padding-Top:0pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:50%; border-top:solid 0.75pt #5B2B82; border-left:solid 0.75pt #5B2B82; border-right:solid 0.75pt #5B2B82;">
<p style="margin-bottom:3pt;margin-top:3pt;margin-left:12.6pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;color:#FFFFFF;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">What we don&#8217;t do:<font style="font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;color:#000000;">&#160;</font></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#E5E5E5" style="padding-left:8pt;padding-Right:0pt;padding-Top:0pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:50%; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #5B2B82; border-left:solid 0.75pt #5B2B82; border-right:solid 0.75pt #5B2B82;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;margin-left:13pt;;margin-right:1.11%;text-indent:-13pt;;color:#5B2B82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Segoe UI Symbol;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#10003;&#160;&#160;<font style="font-style:italic;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;">Require significant stock ownership.</font><font style="font-family:Arial;color:#000000;"> Our stock ownership requirements&#160;&#8211;&#160;including eight times salary for the CEO&#160;&#8211;&#160;are comparable to, or greater than, our Compensation Survey Peer Group peers.</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:7pt;margin-left:12.95pt;;margin-right:1.11%;text-indent:-12.95pt;;color:#5B2B82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Segoe UI Symbol;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#10003;&#160;&#160;<font style="font-style:italic;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;">Require executives to hold equity compensation for at least one year after exercising stock options or vesting of full value awards. </font><font style="font-family:Arial;color:#000000;">Executives must hold net shares upon vesting and net shares acquired upon exercising stock options for at least one year regardless of ownership level.</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:7pt;margin-left:12.95pt;;margin-right:1.11%;text-indent:-12.95pt;;color:#5B2B82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Segoe UI Symbol;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#10003;&#160;&#160;<font style="font-style:italic;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;">Provide for &#8220;clawbacks.&#8221;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;color:#000000;"> Under our recently enhanced policy, we can recoup incentive compensation granted or paid during the last three years upon certain financial restatements or significant misconduct.</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:7pt;margin-left:12.95pt;;margin-right:1.11%;text-indent:-12.95pt;;color:#5B2B82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Segoe UI Symbol;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#10003;&#160;&#160;<font style="font-style:italic;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;">Prohibit hedging, pledging and short sales of our Common Stock.</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:7pt;margin-left:12.95pt;;margin-right:1.11%;text-indent:-12.95pt;;color:#5B2B82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Segoe UI Symbol;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#10003;&#160;&#160;<font style="font-family:Arial;color:#000000;">The </font><font style="font-style:italic;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;">Compensation Committee retains an independent compensation consultant</font><font style="font-family:Arial;color:#000000;">. The consultant does not provide services to the Company other than advising the Compensation Committee.</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:7pt;margin-left:12.95pt;;margin-right:1.11%;text-indent:-12.95pt;;color:#5B2B82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Segoe UI Symbol;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#10003;&#160;&#160;<font style="font-style:italic;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;">Conduct an annual compensation risk assessment</font><font style="font-family:Arial;color:#000000;">.</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:7pt;margin-left:12.95pt;;margin-right:1.11%;text-indent:-12.95pt;;color:#5B2B82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Segoe UI Symbol;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#10003;&#160;&#160;<font style="font-style:italic;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;">Engage with shareholders</font><font style="font-family:Arial;color:#000000;">. We regularly engage shareholders through individual and small-group meetings as well as at major investor conferences. We take input from shareholders into account when designing our compensation programs.</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:7pt;margin-left:12.95pt;;margin-right:1.11%;text-indent:-12.95pt;;color:#5B2B82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Segoe UI Symbol;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#10003;&#160;&#160;<font style="font-style:italic;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;">Offer limited number of perquisites.</font><font style="font-family:Arial;color:#000000;"> To remain competitive in attracting top talent, we offer a limited number of perquisites.</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:7pt;margin-left:12.95pt;;margin-right:1.11%;text-indent:-12.95pt;;color:#5B2B82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Segoe UI Symbol;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#10003;&#160;&#160;<font style="font-style:italic;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;">Pay severance and vest equity only upon a &#8220;double trigger&#8221; in the event of a change in control.</font><font style="font-family:Arial;color:#000000;"> Our double trigger requires both a change in control and termination of the executive&#8217;s employment either without cause or for good reason.&#160;</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:7pt;margin-left:12.95pt;;margin-right:1.11%;text-indent:-12.95pt;;color:#5B2B82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Segoe UI Symbol;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#10003;&#160;&#160;<font style="font-style:italic;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;">Benchmark our executive compensation and our performance against relevant comparators.</font><font style="font-family:Arial;color:#000000;">&#160;</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:7pt;margin-left:12.95pt;;margin-right:1.11%;text-indent:-12.95pt;;color:#5B2B82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Segoe UI Symbol;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#10003;&#160;&#160;<font style="font-style:italic;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;">Determine the majority of compensation based on objective, quantifiable pre-established performance goals.</font><font style="font-family:Arial;color:#000000;">&#160;</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:7pt;margin-left:12.95pt;;margin-right:1.11%;text-indent:-12.95pt;;color:#5B2B82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Segoe UI Symbol;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#10003;&#160;&#160;<font style="font-style:italic;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;">Hold an annual say-on-pay vote.</font><font style="font-family:Arial;color:#000000;">&#160;</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:12.95pt;;margin-right:1.11%;text-indent:-12.95pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:9.5pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#E5E5E5" style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:2pt;padding-Top:0pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:50%; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #5B2B82; border-left:solid 0.75pt #5B2B82; border-right:solid 0.75pt #5B2B82;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;margin-left:25.9pt;;text-indent:-12.95pt;;color:#5B2B82;font-size:10pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:'Times New Roman';"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman'">&#10008;</font><font style="font-style:italic;font-size:9.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;">&#160;&#160; </font><font style="font-style:italic;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;">Provide NEOs with tax gross-ups for perquisites or in the event of a change in control</font><font style="font-family:Arial;color:#000000;">.</font><font style="font-style:italic;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;"> </font><font style="font-family:Arial;color:#000000;">Taxes are the NEOs&#8217; responsibility.</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:7pt;margin-left:25.9pt;;text-indent:-12.95pt;;color:#5B2B82;font-size:10pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:'Times New Roman';"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman'">&#10008;</font><font style="font-style:italic;font-size:9.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;">&#160;&#160; </font><font style="font-style:italic;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;">Re-price or exchange underwater stock options.</font><font style="font-family:Arial;color:#000000;"> We do not re-price outstanding stock options, whether vested or unvested.</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:7pt;margin-left:25.9pt;;text-indent:-12.95pt;;color:#5B2B82;font-size:10pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:'Times New Roman';"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman'">&#10008;</font><font style="font-style:italic;font-size:9.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;">&#160;&#160; </font><font style="font-style:italic;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;">Pay dividends on unvested performance share units unless and until shares are earned.</font><font style="font-family:Arial;color:#000000;"> We do not pay accrued dividend equivalents unless and until the applicable performance targets are met and earned shares are awarded.</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:7pt;margin-left:25.9pt;;text-indent:-12.95pt;;color:#5B2B82;font-size:10pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:'Times New Roman';"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman'">&#10008;</font><font style="font-style:italic;font-size:9.5pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;">&#160;&#160; </font><font style="font-style:italic;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;">Provide separate, enhanced benefit plans for our NEOs.</font><font style="font-family:Arial;color:#000000;"> Our NEOs generally participate in the same retirement, health and welfare plans broadly available to all salaried employees in the location where they are based.</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:7pt;margin-left:27pt;;text-indent:-13.5pt;;color:#5B2B82;font-size:10pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:'Times New Roman';"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman'">&#10008;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;color:#000000;">&#160;&#160; </font><font style="font-style:italic;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;">Incent short-term results to the detriment of long-term goals and results</font><font style="font-family:Arial;color:#000000;">.</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:7pt;margin-left:25.9pt;;text-indent:-12.95pt;;color:#5B2B82;font-size:10pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:'Times New Roman';"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman'">&#10008;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;color:#000000;">&#160;&#160; </font><font style="font-style:italic;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;">Incent excessively risky business strategies</font><font style="font-family:Arial;color:#000000;">.</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:7pt;margin-left:25.9pt;;text-indent:-12.95pt;;color:#5B2B82;font-size:10pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:'Times New Roman';"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:'Times New Roman'">&#10008;</font><font style="font-style:italic;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;">&#160;&#160; Guarantee annual salary increases.</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:25.9pt;;text-indent:-12.95pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:25.9pt;;text-indent:-12.95pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
</tr>
</table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#160;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:1pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<div>
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="center" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top"  style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0pt;padding-Top:0pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:94%;">
<p style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0pt;padding-Top:0pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:6%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td valign="middle"  style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0pt;padding-Top:0pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:94%;">
<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;margin-right:2.96%;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:16pt;font-family:Calibri;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><img src="gycirsmwh4vw000013.jpg" title="" alt="" style="width:85px;height:20px;"></p></td>
<td valign="middle"  BGCOLOR="#683F8B" style="padding-left:4pt;padding-Right:0pt;padding-Top:0pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:6%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:2pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#FFFFFF;font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">45</a></p></td>
</tr>

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:1pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;color:#FCFCFC;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="Background-color:#5B2D83;">&#160;&#160;Compensation Discussion and Analysis&#160;&#160;</font></p>
<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;color:#5A2D82;font-family:Arial;font-size:12pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="PEER_GROUPS_FOR_PAY_PERFORMANCE"></a>Peer Group<a name="PEER_GROUPS_FOR_PAY_PERFORMANCE"></a>s for Pay and Performance</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">As previously referenced in &#8220;Changes to our Executive Compensation Program,&#8221; we use our Compensation Survey Peer Group to benchmark executive compensation against companies of similar size, scope, structure and industry and our Performance Peer Group to assess our relative performance against industry peers.&nbsp;&nbsp; </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Composition and Purpose of our Compensation Survey Peer Group </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Our 2018 Compensation Survey Peer Group is unchanged from 2017 other than reflecting DowDuPont Inc. after the merger of The Dow Chemical Company and E.I. du Pont de Nemours and Company. The median annual revenue of the Compensation Survey Peer Group companies at the time of our 2018 benchmarking was $31.2&#160;billion. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">In determining appropriate compensation levels for our executives, the Compensation Committee reviews compensation levels for comparable roles at companies in our Compensation Survey Peer Group. Aon Hewitt (&#8220;Aon&#8221;) provides the underlying compensation benchmarking data. At the request of the Compensation Committee, CAP reviews and evaluates Aon&#8217;s data. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">As previously mentioned, we made changes to our Compensation Survey Peer Group for 2019 to better reflect our size and complexity. See &#8220;Changes to our Executive Compensation Program&#8221; for additional information.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-style:italic;color:#5B2B82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Competitive Positioning </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Compensation Committee&#8217;s compensation strategy is to benchmark total direct compensation (at target levels), including base salary and annual and long-term incentives, at or near the median of our Compensation Survey Peer Group. Company and individual performance will determine whether actual compensation received is above or below the Compensation Survey Peer Group median. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">To further validate our compensation levels, using data provided by CAP, the Compensation Committee retrospectively evaluates how well we aligned pay-for-performance compared with our Compensation Survey Peer Group. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Composition and Purpose of our Performance Peer Group </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We compare our financial and TSR performance against our Performance Peer Group. The Performance Peer Group comparison allows us to link long-term incentive compensation directly to the delivery of superior financial results relative to our food and beverage industry peers. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Industry competitors primarily focused on the production and marketing of food and non-alcoholic beverages, regardless of revenue size or market capitalization, comprise our 2018 Performance Peer Group. We directly compete with these companies, so comparing our results with this peer group&#8217;s performance provides a valuable and relevant measure of our performance. Specifically, we compare our annualized TSR with the median annualized TSR of our Performance Peer Group to assess our results against the TSR performance measure for our performance share units. This group of companies is less relevant when we compare compensation levels for certain executive positions because differences in company size and complexity reduce comparability. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:1pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:12pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><img src="gycirsmwh4vw000106.jpg" title="" alt="" style="width:427px;height:209px;"></p>

<td valign="top"  style="width:94%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>

<td valign="middle"  style="width:94%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:16pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;color:#5A2D82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">2019 Proxy Statement</p></td>

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:1pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;color:#FCFCFC;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="Background-color:#5B2D83;">&#160;&#160;Compensation Discussion and Analysis&#160;&#160;</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;color:#5A2D82;font-family:Arial;font-size:12pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU55"></a><a name="INDIVIDUAL_EXECUTIVE_COMPENSATION_PROGRA"></a><font style="font-weight:bold;color:#5A2D82;font-family:Arial;font-size:12pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="INDIVIDUAL_EXECUTIVE_COMPENSATION_PROGRA"></a>Individual Executive Compe</font><font style="font-weight:bold;color:#5A2D82;font-family:Arial;font-size:12pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">nsation Program Elements </font></p>
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We do not generally enter into employment agreements with any of our NEOs beyond their initial offer and transition compensation. All U.S.-based NEOs, including our CEO, are &#8220;at will&#8221; employees. This table identifies and describes the primary elements of the 2018 executive compensation program for our NEOs, including detail on each element&#8217;s specific program objective. A more detailed discussion, including definitions of the financial measures used in our Annual Cash Incentive Program and performance share unit grants, can be found in Annex A. We discuss individual compensation decisions for each NEO later in this section. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<td valign="top"  style="width:20%; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-right:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">

<td valign="top"  style="width:46.66%; border-top:solid 0.75pt #5B2B82; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-left:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-right:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:3pt;margin-top:3pt;margin-left:7.2pt;;margin-right:0.56%;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Ongoing cash compensation based on NEO role, responsibilities, experience, market data and individual performance.</p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="width:33.34%; border-top:solid 0.75pt #5B2B82; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-left:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:3pt;margin-left:20.2pt;;text-indent:-13pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;Attract and retain talent</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:4pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#160;</p>

<tr>
<td valign="top"  style="width:20%; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #5B2B82; border-right:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:3pt;margin-top:3pt;margin-left:3.6pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Annual Cash </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:3pt;margin-top:3pt;margin-left:3.6pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Incentive Program</p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="width:46.66%; border-top:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #5B2B82; border-left:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-right:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:3pt;margin-top:3pt;margin-left:7.2pt;;margin-right:0.56%;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Annual cash incentive with a target award for each NEO. Actual awards may be higher or lower than target based on Company, business and individual performance. Awards range between 0% and 200% of target based on performance.</p></td>

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:4pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#160;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:41.8pt;;text-indent:-21.6pt;;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8211;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Through rigorous financial goals</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:4pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#160;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:41.8pt;;text-indent:-21.6pt;;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8211;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Through individual contribution</p>

<p style="margin-bottom:1pt;margin-top:3pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Equity Program</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td valign="top"  style="padding-left:8pt;padding-Right:0pt;padding-Top:0pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:20%; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-right:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:3pt;margin-top:3pt;margin-left:-3.6pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Performance Share Units (75%)</p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="width:46.66%; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-right:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:12pt;margin-top:3pt;margin-left:7.2pt;;margin-right:0.56%;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Each NEO receives a target annual grant of performance share units at the outset of a three-year performance cycle based upon the NEO&#8217;s role and long-term individual performance.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:7.2pt;;margin-right:0.56%;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Actual awards are determined at the end of the performance cycle&#160;by evaluating financial performance against pre-determined&nbsp;&nbsp;targets. Awards range between 0% and 200% of target based on performance. Awards are delivered in Common Stock.</p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="width:33.34%; border-top:solid 0.75pt #5B2B82; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-left:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:4pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#160;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:20.2pt;;text-indent:-13pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;Drive top-tier performance</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:4pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#160;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:33.55pt;;text-indent:-15.5pt;;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8211;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Through rigorous financial and market measures</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:4pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#160;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:41.8pt;;text-indent:-21.6pt;;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8211;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Focus on long-term sustained success</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:4pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#160;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:16.7pt;;text-indent:-9.5pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;Enhance stock ownership/align with shareholder interests</font></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td valign="top"  style="padding-left:8pt;padding-Right:0pt;padding-Top:0pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:20%; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-right:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:3pt;margin-top:3pt;margin-left:-3.6pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Non-Qualified Stock Options (&#8220;NQSOs&#8221;) (25%)</p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="width:46.66%; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-right:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:3pt;margin-top:3pt;margin-left:7.2pt;;margin-right:0.56%;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Each NEO receives an annual grant of NQSOs based upon the NEO&#8217;s role and long-term individual performance. The NQSOs vest:</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:4pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#160;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:20.2pt;;text-indent:-13pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;33% on the first and second anniversary of the grant date; and</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:4pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#160;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:3pt;margin-top:3pt;margin-left:20.2pt;;text-indent:-13pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;34% on the third anniversary of the grant date.</font></p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="width:33.34%; border-top:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-left:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:3pt;margin-top:3pt;margin-left:18pt;;text-indent:-10.8pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;Attract, motivate and retain talent</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:4pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#160;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:16.7pt;;text-indent:-9.5pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;Enhance stock ownership/align with shareholder interests </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:4pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#160;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:16.7pt;;text-indent:-9.5pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;Link realized value solely to stock price appreciation</font></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td valign="top"  style="padding-left:8pt;padding-Right:0pt;padding-Top:0pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:20%; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #5B2B82; border-right:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:3pt;margin-top:3pt;margin-left:-3.6pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Deferred Stock Units</p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="width:46.66%; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #5B2B82; border-right:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:3pt;margin-top:3pt;margin-left:7.2pt;;margin-right:0.56%;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We grant deferred stock units to NEOs only in specific new hire and retention situations. The vesting periods for deferred stock unit grants vary but are typically up to three years.</p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="width:33.34%; border-top:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #5B2B82; border-left:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:3pt;margin-top:3pt;margin-left:18pt;;text-indent:-10.8pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;Attract and/or retain critical talent</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:4pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#160;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:3pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:16.7pt;;text-indent:-9.5pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;Enhance stock ownership/align with shareholder interests</font></p></td>
</tr>
</table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><br /></p>

<td valign="middle"  style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0pt;padding-Top:0pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:94%;">
<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;margin-right:2.96%;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:16pt;font-family:Calibri;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><img src="gycirsmwh4vw000013.jpg" title="" alt="" style="width:85px;height:20px;"></p></td>

</table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:1pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;color:#FCFCFC;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="Background-color:#5B2D83;">&#160;&#160;Compensation Discussion and Analysis&#160;&#160;</font></p>
<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU56"></a><font style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Total T</font><font style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">arget Compensation Mix</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The charts below compare the 2018 total target compensation mix for our CEO and, on average, our other NEOs serving as executive officers on December 31, 2018 with the average of the companies in our Compensation Survey Peer Group. This compensation mix includes base pay, target annual incentive and long-term incentive grants. The charts show that our target compensation mix aligns closely with that of our Compensation Survey Peer Group. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:12pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><img src="gycirsmwh4vw000108.jpg" title="" alt="" style="width:575px;height:202px;"></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:12pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><img src="gycirsmwh4vw000109.jpg" title="" alt="" style="width:579px;height:203px;"></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Base Salary </p>
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-style:italic;color:#5B2B82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Overview </p>
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Base salary is the only element of compensation that is fixed. In setting base salaries for our NEOs, the Compensation Committee generally starts by targeting base salary at or near the median of our Compensation Survey Peer Group based on the executive&#8217;s comparable role. The Compensation Committee then considers several other factors, including NEO performance, level of responsibility, experience, potential to assume roles with greater responsibility and, if relevant, host country salary data. The Compensation Committee reviews NEO salaries annually. If awarded, salary increases for executive officers are generally effective April&#160;1. </p>
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">If there is a notable change in an executive officer&#8217;s role and responsibilities during the year, the Compensation Committee considers whether an increase is warranted. </p>
<p style="margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-style:italic;color:#5B2B82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">2018 Compensation Actions </p>
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Mr. Zaramella&#8217;s annual base salary was increased to $700,000 on August 1, 2018 when he became Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer (&#8220;CFO&#8221;) and completed an international permanent transfer to the United States. The Compensation Committee set his base salary below the median of our Compensation Survey Peer Group with the expectation of bringing Mr. Zaramella&#8217;s base salary to parity with the peer group based on performance over time. In April 2018, prior to his appointment as CFO, Mr. Zaramella received a base salary increase based on his individual performance assessment in his previous role.</p>
<div>

<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:2pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#FFFFFF;font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">48</a></p></td>
<td valign="middle"  style="width:94%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:16pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;color:#5A2D82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">2019 Proxy Statement</p></td>

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:1pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;color:#FCFCFC;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="Background-color:#5B2D83;">&#160;&#160;Compensation Discussion and Analysis&#160;&#160;</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU57"></a><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Effective as of her June 11, 2018 start date, Ms. Alviti&#8217;s annual base salary is $600,000. The Compensation Committee set Ms. Alviti&#8217;s base salary at the median of our Compensation Survey Peer Group to reflect her several years of experience as a Chief Human Resources Officer (&#8220;CHRO&#8221;) at her previous employer.</font></p>
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">None of our other NEOs received a base salary increase in 2018. </p>
<p style="margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Annual Incentive Program </p>
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-style:italic;color:#5B2B82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Overview </p>
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We design our Annual Cash Incentive Program to motivate our NEOs to achieve or exceed our annual financial and strategic goals. The Compensation Committee sets the formula, target, threshold and maximum annual incentive opportunities at the beginning of each year. Targets are set based on internal financial and operating plans for the year as well as external market factors. The Compensation Committee determines actual awards earned by an NEO on annual financial results and individual NEO performance. Annual incentive award payouts can vary greatly from year-to-year based on actual Company financial performance as well as individual performance relative to the target goals. </p>
<p style="margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-style:italic;color:#5B2B82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Annual Incentive Program Award Formula </p>
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Compensation Committee used the formula below to determine the awards to NEOs under the 2018 Annual Incentive Program. The Financial Result Weighting increased to 80% in 2018 (from 60% in 2017) and the Individual Performance Weighting decreased to 20% in 2018 (from 40% in 2017). </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#160;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:12pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><img src="gycirsmwh4vw000110.jpg" title="" alt="" style="width:671px;height:234px;"></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:5pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> lry as of December&#160;31,2018 target annual incentive opportunity (% of base salary)= target annual incentive amount target annual incentive amount financial result weighting (80%) corporate rating (0-200%) target annual incentive amount individual performance weighting (20%) individual performance rating (0-200%) actual program award </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><br /></p>

<td valign="middle"  style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0pt;padding-Top:0pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:94%;">
<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;margin-right:2.96%;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:16pt;font-family:Calibri;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><img src="gycirsmwh4vw000013.jpg" title="" alt="" style="width:85px;height:20px;"></p></td>

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:1pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;color:#FCFCFC;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="Background-color:#5B2D83;">&#160;&#160;Compensation Discussion and Analysis&#160;&#160;</font></p>
<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU58"></a><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">In setting the target annual incentive opportunity for each NEO, the Compensation Committee annually reviews benchmark data from our Compensation Survey Peer Group. Based on the data for the executive&#8217;s comparable role, the Compensation Committee generally sets the target annual incentive opportunity at or near the median of our Compensation Survey Peer Group. The chart below describes each of the Annual Incentive Program elements. </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<div>
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="center" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td style="width:26.62%;"></td>
<td style="width:73.38%;"></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td valign="bottom"  style=" border-bottom:solid 1pt #5B2B82;">
<p style="margin-bottom:1pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:3.6pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#5B2B82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Annual Incentive<br />Program Element</p></td>
<td valign="bottom"  style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0pt;padding-Top:0pt;padding-Bottom:0pt; border-bottom:solid 1pt #5B2B82;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#5B2B82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Key Provisions</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#E6E1EE">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:3.6pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Target Annual Incentive</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:1pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:3.6pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Opportunity</p></td>
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#E6E1EE">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The 2018 target annual incentive opportunity is a target percentage of base salary <font style="font-size:9.5pt;">and</font> reflects the role and responsibility of each NEO:</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:4pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#160;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:18pt;;text-indent:-18pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:9.5pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;<font style="font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Mr.</font><font style="color:#000000;">&#160;</font><font style="font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Van de Put: 150%</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:4pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#160;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:18pt;;text-indent:-18pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:9.5pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;<font style="font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Mr.</font><font style="color:#000000;">&#160;</font><font style="font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Gladden and Mr. Cofer: 100%</font></p>
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:18.25pt;;text-indent:-18.25pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="font-size:9.5pt;font-family:Arial;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;color:#000000;">Mr. Zaramella: 100% effective August 1, 2018 </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:18.25pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(55% January 1, 2018 through July 31, 2018)</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:18pt;;text-indent:-18pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="font-size:9.5pt;font-family:Arial;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;</font><font style="font-family:Arial;color:#000000;">Mr. Walter: 90%</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:4pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#160;</p>

<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#000000;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">134%</p></td>
</tr>
</table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:3.4%;text-indent:-3.4%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Overall, we achieved an above target performance rating of 134% for Corporate under the 2018 Annual Cash Incentive Program. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;color:#5B2B82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">2<font style="font-style:italic;">018 North America Rating</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">To determine the award for Mr. Walter, the Compensation Committee first evaluated the 2018 North America results against the 2018 North America performance targets: </p>

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:3.4%;text-indent:-3.4%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">This performance resulted in a rating of 76% for North America under the 2018 Annual Cash Incentive Program. The Compensation Committee considered the targets, actual results and overall business unit rating in North America in determining the final 2018 award for Mr.&#160;Walter. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-top:8pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-style:italic;color:#5B2B82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Individual Performance Ratings </p>
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;letter-spacing:-0.2pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">At the beginning of each year, based on the annual financial and strategic plan, our CEO and the other NEOs develop annual quantitative and qualitative objectives. Our CEO discusses his objectives with the Compensation Committee. Following this discussion and input, the Compensation Committee approves the CEO&#8217;s annual goals. </p>
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">At the conclusion of the annual performance period: </p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:5.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">Our CEO provides a detailed review of his performance relative to his annual objectives to the full Board. After consultation with the full Board, the Compensation Committee determines the CEO&#8217;s individual performance rating. </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:5.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">For each of the other NEOs, the CEO provides the Compensation Committee with an individual performance assessment and rating recommendation based on the NEO&#8217;s contributions in specific areas, such as achievement of key strategic initiatives, operational efficiency, enterprise leadership, quality of financial results and talent management. The Compensation Committee reviews and discusses the recommendations made by the CEO before determining each NEO&#8217;s individual performance rating. </font></p></td></tr></table></div>

<p style="margin-top:4pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:7.9pt;;text-indent:-7.9pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:8pt;">&#160;&#160;</font><font style="font-size:8pt;">Revitalized the Company&#8217;s orientation around strategic marketing.</font></p>
<p style="margin-top:4pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:7.9pt;;text-indent:-7.9pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:8pt;">&#160;&#160;</font><font style="font-size:8pt;">Delivered strong e-commerce growth.</font></p>
<p style="margin-top:4pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:8.15pt;;text-indent:-8pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:8pt;">&#160;&#160;</font><font style="font-size:8pt;">Developed a new, more agile, approach to innovation and renovation, including the&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:7.15pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">creation of <font style="font-style:italic;">SnackFutures, </font>a disruptive Innovation and Venture Hub within </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:7.15pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Mondel&#275;z International.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr style="height:62.55pt;">
<td valign="top"  style="width:13.14%; border-bottom:solid 1pt #5B2B82;">
<p style="margin-top:2pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#160;&#160;Mr. Walter</p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="width:31%; border-bottom:solid 1pt #5B2B82;">
<p style="margin-top:2pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:8pt;;text-indent:-8pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:8pt;">&#160;&#160;</font><font style="font-size:8pt;">Achieve key financial goals for the North</font><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:8pt;"> </font><font style="font-size:8pt;">America region (see performance goals in &#8220;2018 North America Rating&#8221;)</font></p>
<p style="margin-top:2pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:8pt;;text-indent:-8pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:8pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="width:55.86%; border-bottom:solid 1pt #5B2B82;">
<p style="margin-top:2pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Mr.&#160;Walter&#8217;s individual performance rating reflects the following:</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:3pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:8pt;;text-indent:-8pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:8pt;">&#160;&#160;</font><font style="font-size:8pt;">North America demonstrated progress against its turnaround objectives: </font></p>
<p style="margin-top:4pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:15.8pt;;text-indent:-7.9pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:8pt;">&#160;&#160;</font><font style="font-size:8pt;">Over-delivered versus target Organic Net Revenue Growth, volume growth and market share growth</font> </p>
<p style="margin-top:4pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:15.8pt;;text-indent:-7.9pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:8pt;">&#160;&#160;</font><font style="font-size:8pt;">Did not achieve Adjusted Gross Margin Percent and Adjusted OI target; however, Adjusted OI did grow versus prior year</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:4pt;margin-top:4pt;margin-left:15.8pt;;text-indent:-7.9pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:8pt;">&#160;&#160;</font><font style="font-size:8pt;">Free Cash Flow at target</font></p></td>

<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;color:#FCFCFC;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="Background-color:#5B2D83;">&#160;&#160;Compensation Discussion and Analysis&#160;&#160;</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-style:italic;color:#5B2B82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU61"></a><font style="font-style:italic;color:#5B2B82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Annual Cash Incentive Program Decisions </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Compensation Committee retains discretionary authority to adjust the final Corporate and North America ratings (up or down) by as much as 25 percentage points (&#8220;pp&#8221;) to recognize more subjective, less quantifiable factors&#160;&#8211;&#160;such as how well we performed based on compliance, diversity and the quality of our results. The Compensation Committee did not adjust any 2018 performance ratings. </p>
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">After determining the 2018 corporate rating and each NEO&#8217;s individual performance against the annual objectives described above, the Compensation Committee approved the following annual incentive cash payments: </p>

<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(1)</sup> Mr. Zaramella&#8217;s 2018 annual incentive award was prorated at a 55% target through July 31, 2018; from August 1, 2018 through December 31, 2018 his target was 100%.</p>
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(</sup><sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">2</sup><sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">)</sup> Mr. Gladden received a prorated 2018 annual incentive award for service through July 31, 2018 based on actual individual and Company performance for his 2018 employment at the Company. He did not receive any other compensation upon separation from the Company and forfeited his outstanding long-term incentive grants.</p>
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(</sup><sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">3</sup><sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">)</sup> Ms. Alviti&#8217;s 2018 annual incentive award was prorated based on her June 11, 2018 hire date.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:2.5%;text-indent:-2.5%;font-family:Times New Roman;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Equity Program </p>
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-style:italic;color:#5B2B82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Overview </p>
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We design our equity grants to align our executive officers&#8217; and shareholders&#8217; interests. For our 2018 equity program, the Compensation Committee used the same mix used in 2017: 75% performance share units and 25% NQSOs. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:12pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><img src="gycirsmwh4vw000113.jpg" title="" alt="" style="width:476px;height:215px;"></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Compensation Committee develops target long-term incentive grants based on an analysis of competitive target grant levels that approximate the median total long-term incentives of our Compensation Survey Peer Group. The Compensation Committee may make an equity grant to an NEO above or below target based on the Compensation Committee&#8217;s qualitative review of the NEO&#8217;s individual performance. Generally, the equity grant value is between 50% and 150% of the target. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;color:#FFFFFF;font-size:1pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">2017 equity program 75% performance share units incents achievement of long-term operational objectives strengthens retention facilitates stock ownership strengthens ties to shareholders 25% NQSOs requires share price appreciation for value creation strengthens retention facilitates stock ownership strengthens ties to shareholders 25% adjusted ROIC increase 25% organic net revenue growth 50% annualized relative TSR </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
