<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">canceling some or all of the covered executive or executive officer&#8217;s restricted stock or deferred stock unit grants, performance share units and outstanding stock options; </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:8%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">adjusting the covered executive or executive officer&#8217;s future compensation; </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:8%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">terminating the covered executive or executive officer; and/or </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:8%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">initiating legal action against the covered executive or executive officer. </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;color:#5A2D82;font-family:Arial;font-size:12pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="OUR_TRADING_RESTRICTIONS_ANTIHEDGING_POL"></a><a name="OUR_TRADING_RESTRICTIONS_ANTIHEDGING_POL"></a>Our Trading Restrictions, Anti-Hedging and Anti-Pledging Policy</p>
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Our insider trading policy limits the timing and types of transactions in Mondel&#275;z International securities by Section&#160;16 officers, including our NEOs (and any member of the Section&#160;16 officer&#8217;s family sharing the same household, any corporations or other business entities they control or manage and any trusts of which they are the trustee or otherwise have investment control over). Among other restrictions, the policy: </p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">allows Section&#160;16 officers to trade Company securities only during open window periods and only after they have pre-cleared transactions with the Corporate Secretary; </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">prohibits Section&#160;16 officers from short-selling Company securities or &#8220;selling against the box&#8221; (failing to deliver sold securities); and </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">prohibits Section&#160;16 officers from entering into transactions in puts, calls or other derivatives on Mondel&#275;z International securities on an exchange or in any other organized market, as well as any other derivative or hedging transactions on Mondel&#275;z International securities. </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Our insider trading policy also prohibits our executive officers and certain additional executives from holding Mondel&#275;z International securities in a margin account or pledging Mondel&#275;z International securities as collateral for a&#160;loan. </p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;color:#5A2D82;font-family:Arial;font-size:12pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="OUR_POLICY_ON_QUALIFYING_COMPENSATION_FO"></a><a name="OUR_POLICY_ON_QUALIFYING_COMPENSATION_FO"></a>Our Policy on Qualifying Compensation for Tax Deductibility </p>
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Section&#160;162(m) of the Code generally places a limit of $1 million per year on the amount of deductible compensation paid to certain "covered employees," which includes our named executive officers. Section 162(m) exempted from this limitation "qualified performance-based compensation" with respect to taxable years beginning on or before December 31, 2017. Recent changes to the Code provide for a transition rule that continues to exempt qualified performance-based compensation that is payable pursuant to a binding written agreement in effect on November 2, 2017 but otherwise generally repeals the exemption for performance-based compensation. Historically, our annual incentive payout and long-term incentive grants were intended to be deductible under Section&#160;162(m). The Committee did, however, reserve the right to, in its sole discretion, pay compensation that was not deductible under Section&#160;162(m) if it determined that paying such compensation was needed in order to attract, retain or provide incentives to our NEOs, or was otherwise desirable. Given complexities in the tax rules, it is also possible that compensation intended to qualify for the qualified performance-based compensation exception did not so qualify. The Committee believes that shareholder interests are best served if it retains discretion and flexibility in awarding compensation. Even though some compensation awards may result in non-deductible compensation expenses, the Committee intends to maintain strong pay-for-performance alignment of executive compensation arrangements notwithstanding loss of deductibility for certain compensation due to the repeal of the exemption for performance-based compensation.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:8pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(1) For Mr. Zaramella, this amount includes an accrued vacation payout in connection with his August 1, 2018 localization to the United States. This payout was paid in Swiss francs, and the values for this table have been converted to U.S. dollars using the conversion rate on December&#160;31, 2018 (the &#8220;Exchange Rate&#8221;). For Mr. Gladden, this amount includes an accrued vacation payout due to his separation from the Company.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(2) Reflects the portion of Ms. Alviti&#8217;s sign on award paid in cash in 2018. Ms. Alviti will need to re-pay this amount if she leaves the company prior to June 11, 2020. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(3) Reflects grants of deferred stock units and performance share units. The amounts shown represent the full grant date fair value of the stock grants made in each year as computed in accordance with FASB ASC Topic 718. Assumptions used in the calculation of these amounts are included in Note 11 to the consolidated financial statements contained in our 2018 Form 10-K. For performance share units, the amounts are based on the probable outcome of the performance conditions as of the grant date. Below is a breakout of the applicable 2018-2020, 2017-2019 and 2016-2018 performance share unit grants for each NEO assuming maximum performance. Mr.&#160;Zaramella&#8217;s two 2018-2020 performance share unit grants have the same terms, consistent with the annual grant. Ms. Alviti&#8217;s grant, which was made on her date of hire, has the same terms as the annual grant. </p>

<td valign="bottom"  BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0.75pt;padding-Top:0.75pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:1.98%; border-top:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-right:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#FF0000;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&nbsp;</p></td>

<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#000000;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">566,836</p></td>
<td valign="bottom"  BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0.75pt;padding-Top:0.75pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:2.06%; border-top:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-right:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#FF0000;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&nbsp;</p></td>

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:4.54%;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(a) Consistent with the findings of an independent, third-party security study, for security and personal safety, we require Mr.&#160;Van de Put to use a private (non-commercial) aircraft for all travel. Mr.&#160;Van de Put used a Company-leased aircraft for all travel. The incremental cost of personal use of the Company-leased aircraft, as reflected in the table, is the actual invoice to the Company. Mr.&#160;Van de Put is responsible for taxes in connection with his personal aircraft use and we do not reimburse him for those taxes. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:4.54%;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(b) All U.S. executive officers are eligible for an annual financial counseling allowance up to $7,500 and, in the case of Mr.&#160;Van de Put, up to $10,000. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:4.54%;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(c) All eligible U.S. employees, including our NEOs, receive matching Company contributions for contributions made to the Mondel&#275;z Global LLC Thrift Plan and Mondel&#275;z Global LLC Supplemental Benefits Plan I, if applicable. Similarly, all eligible U.S. employees hired or localized to the United States after 2008 who are not otherwise eligible to participate in the Mondel&#275;z Global LLC Retirement Plan, including Mr.&#160;Van de Put, Mr. Zaramella, Mr.&#160;Gladden, Ms. Alviti and Mr.&#160;Walter, receive an additional non-elective Company contribution to the Mondel&#275;z Global LLC Thrift Plan and Mondel&#275;z Global LLC Supplemental Benefits Plan I, if applicable, equal to 4.5% of eligible compensation. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:4.54%;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(d) At the time of his hire, Mr. Walter received our standard executive relocation assistance program, which covers moving, travel and other expenses in connection with his international relocation. Tax payments are also provided to cover the additional taxes due solely to the relocation assistance program in accordance with the policy. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:4.54%;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(e) Mr.&#160;Zaramella, a Swiss expatriate, received payments in conjunction with his international assignment in the United States until his localization effective August 1, 2018. These payments were similar to the types of payments generally made to other employees who accept an international assignment with the Company. Payments are designed to mitigate the inconvenience of an international assignment by covering expenses for an expatriate in excess of what the expatriate would have incurred if the employee had remained in his or her home country. These payments include housing expenses, cost of living adjustments, travel expenses and other assignment related expenses. Expenses incurred in Switzerland in Swiss francs are converted to U.S. dollars using the Exchange Rate. The tax equalization payments are made pursuant to our Tax Equalization Policy and are designed to cover the additional taxes, if any, that an employee incurs due solely to the international assignment. The tax equalization amount is negative due to the fact that the effective Swiss tax rate, which Mr.&#160;Zaramella was responsible for while on assignment, is higher than the effective U.S. tax rate. Mr.&#160;Zaramella also received a benefit associated with the Company selected tax services provider preparing his required tax returns. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:4.54%;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Mr. Cofer, a former U.S. expatriate who repatriated back to the United States in 2016, had residual assignment-related tax expenses; however, the tax equalization amount is negative due to the amount and timing of repayments related to tax equalization settlements. Mr.&#160;Cofer also received a benefit associated with the Company-selected tax services provider preparing his required tax returns. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:4.54%;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(f) Generally, all salaried employees in the United States are eligible for a computer allowance under our Bring Your Own Computer Program, which allows eligible employees to purchase a computer of their choice for work purposes. Mr. Walter received a payment under this program. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:4.54%;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(g) Mr. Van de Put and Mr. Walter each incurred a business-related tax expense associated with business travel to Canada. As the travel was business-related, the Company paid the Canadian tax expense on their behalf and the associated tax gross-up. </p>

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:10pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(1) Table does not include a &#8220;threshold&#8221; column because under our 2018 AIP a zero payout was possible if threshold performance levels were not achieved and individual performance did not warrant a payout. Actual amounts under our 2018 AIP were settled in March 2019 and are disclosed in the Non-Equity Incentive Plan Compensation Annual Incentive Awards column in the 2018 Summary Compensation Table. The maximum amounts equal 200% of target. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(2) No threshold column is included because a zero payout is possible if threshold performance levels are not achieved. The target number of units shown in the table reflects the number of shares of our Common Stock earned if performance is achieved at target levels. Actual shares earned under the 2018-2020 performance cycle will be issued no later than March&#160;15, 2021 assuming threshold performance is achieved. All shares will be awarded net of applicable tax withholding. Dividend equivalents accrue during the performance cycle and will be paid out at the end of the performance cycle in cash, net of applicable tax withholding, based on the actual number of shares earned for the performance cycle, if any. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(3) Dividend equivalents are generally paid on unvested deferred stock units at a similar time as dividends are paid to our shareholders. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(4) Exercise price equals the closing price of our Common Stock on the grant date. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(5) Amounts represent the grant date fair value of the awards as computed in accordance with FASB ASC Topic 718. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>

The amounts also include earned dividend equivalents for deferred stock units and accrued dividend equivalents for performance share units based on the actual share award for the 2016-2018 performance cycle. <td valign="middle"  BGCOLOR="#E6E1EE" style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0.75pt;padding-Top:0.75pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:2.72%; border-top:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-right:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#FF0000;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="middle"  BGCOLOR="#E6E1EE" style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0.75pt;padding-Top:0.75pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:12.06%; border-top:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-left:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-right:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#000000;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8211;</p></td>

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(1) No U.S.-based salaried employee hired after 2008 or localized to the United States after 2015 is eligible to participate in the Mondel&#275;z Global LLC <font style="color:#000000;">Retirement Plan. Therefore, no amounts are shown for Mr. Van de Put, Mr. Zaramella, Mr.&#160;Gladden, Ms. Alviti and Mr. Walter. Mr. Zaramella was a participant in the Pension Fund Mondelez Switzerland. </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(2) The years of credited service under the plans are equivalent to the years of total service for each NEO except for Mr. Zaramella. For Mr.&#160;Zaramella, the years of credited service is through July&#160;31, 2018 when he localized to the United States and was required to take a distribution from the Pension Fund Mondelez Switzerland. This plan pays benefits in Swiss francs; the values for this table have been converted to U.S. dollars using the Exchange Rate. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;color:#000000;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(3) For Mr.&#160;Cofer, the amount reflects the actuarial present value of benefits accumulated under the respective retirement plans, in accordance with the same assumptions and measurement dates <font style="color:#000000;">disclosed</font> in <font style="color:#000000;">Note 10 </font>to the consolidated financial statements contained in our 2018 Form 10-K. The assumptions for each of the plans are as follows: </p>
<div align="left">

<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">

<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#000000;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#000000;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#000000;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:8pt;">Assumes commencement at the earliest age that participants would be eligible for an unreduced pension benefit, which is age 62, and are discounted for current age; </p></td></tr></table></div>

<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">

<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#000000;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:8pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#000000;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#000000;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#000000;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:8pt;">Discount rate of 4.41% (Mondel&#275;z Global LLC Retirement Plan) and 4.40% (Mondel&#275;z Global LLC Supplemental Benefits Plan I); and </p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#000000;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:8pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#000000;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#000000;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#000000;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:8pt;">RP2014 Mortality Table Projected on a Generational Basis with MP2018. </p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;color:#5A2D82;font-family:Arial;font-size:12pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="RETIREMENT_BENEFIT_PLAN_DESCRIPTIONS"></a><a name="RETIREMENT_BENEFIT_PLAN_DESCRIPTIONS"></a>Retirement Benefit Plan Descriptions </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Mondel&#275;z Global LLC Retirement Plan&#160;&#8211;&#160;Mr.&#160;Cofer </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Eligibility for this plan is limited to U.S.-based employees who were eligible for the Kraft Foods Group, Inc. Retirement Plan before our October&#160;1, 2012 spin-off of KFG. As a result, only full-time and part-time U.S. employees, including our NEOs, hired by the Company before January&#160;1, 2009 or localized to the United States before 2016 are participants in this funded non-contributory, tax-qualified defined benefit plan. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Benefits under this plan are payable upon retirement in the form of an annuity or a lump sum. Normal retirement under this plan is defined as age 65 with five years of vesting service. If a participant elects to receive a distribution prior to normal retirement, benefits are subject to reduction. Participants vest on completing five years of service. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Benefits under the plan generally accrue based on: </p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:10%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">1.3% of final average pay up to the Social Security covered compensation amount multiplied by years of service up to 30; plus </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:10%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">1.675% of final average pay in excess of the Social Security covered compensation amount, multiplied by years of service up to 30; plus </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:10%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.33%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">0.5% of final average pay multiplied by years of service in excess of 30. </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Final average pay is defined as the greater of (a)&#160;the average of an executive officer&#8217;s salary plus annual bonus during the last 60 consecutive months of service before separation and (b)&#160;the five highest consecutive calendar years of salary plus annual bonus out of the last ten years prior to separation. Social Security covered compensation is an amount equal to the average of the Social Security taxable wage bases for the 35-year period that ends in the year the participant reaches age 65. (If the participant was born between 1938 and 1954, the 35-year average ends in the year the participant reaches age 66. If the participant was born after 1954, the 35-year average ends in the year the participant reaches age 67.) The Internal Revenue Service has established certain limits on how much employees may receive from this plan. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Employees hired before January&#160;1, 2004 with at least ten years of service are eligible to retire under this plan at age&#160;55. The benefits payable to employees eligible to retire before age 62 are reduced by 3% each year (maximum 20%) between age 62 and the year that the employee retires. </p>
<div>

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
</tr>

<td valign="middle"  style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0pt;padding-Top:0pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:94%;">

<td valign="middle"  BGCOLOR="#683F8B" style="padding-left:4pt;padding-Right:0pt;padding-Top:0pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:6%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:2pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#FFFFFF;font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">69</a></p></td>
</tr>

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:1pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;color:#FCFCFC;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="Background-color:#5B2D83;">&#160;&#160;Executive Compensation Tables</font><font style="Background-color:#5B2B82;">&#160;&#160;</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU76"></a><font style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Mondel&#275;z Global LLC Supplemental Benefits Plan I&#160;&#8211;&#160;Mr.&#160;Cofer </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We offer an unfunded, non-qualified pension plan as part of the Mondel&#275;z Global LLC Supplemental Benefits Plan I to keep affected U.S.-based executives whole when they are not able to receive a benefit to which they would otherwise be entitled under the Mondel&#275;z Global LLC Retirement Plan due to its status as a tax-qualified plan. If the executive&#8217;s qualified pension plan benefit would be limited due to qualified plan compensation or benefit limits under the Code, then the non-qualified pension plan provides the executive with the total pension benefit to which the executive would be entitled absent the applicable qualified plan limits under the Code offset by the benefit payable under the qualified pension plan. Similarly, if the executive deferred base salary or incentive compensation under the Mondel&#275;z Global LLC Executive Deferred Compensation Plan, then the deferred compensation is considered non-qualified earnings and the pension benefit relating to the deferred compensation is payable from the non-qualified pension plan. Only employees who have an accrued benefit under our tax-qualified pension plan are eligible to receive a supplemental non-qualified pension benefit under our non-qualified pension plan. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Employees hired before January&#160;1, 2004 with at least ten years of service are eligible to retire under our non-qualified pension plan at age 55. The benefits payable to employees eligible to retire before age 62 are reduced by 3% each year (maximum 20%) between age 62 and the year that the employee retires. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Pension Fund Mondelez Switzerland&#160;&#8211;&#160;Mr. Zaramella </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Eligibility for this defined benefit plan is limited to employees with a Swiss employment contract signed before January&#160;1, 2011. Benefits under the plan generally accrue based on 1.85% of the coordination deduction for each year of credited service up to a maximum of 37 years. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Pensionable salary corresponds to annual base salary minus a coordination deduction. The coordination deduction is the amount of pay that is insured by the pension fund and cannot be more than 40% of salary and may not exceed 100% of the maximum State Social Security. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Normal retirement under this plan is defined as age 65 and benefits under this plan are payable upon retirement in the form of an annuity or a lump sum. If a participant elects to receive a distribution prior to normal retirement, benefits are subject to reduction. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Upon termination of employment in Switzerland, the present value of the accrued pension would be transferred to the plan participant&#8217;s new employer&#8217;s occupational benefits institution, assuming employment continues in Switzerland. If the plan participant is leaving Switzerland permanently, the plan participant can request either the funds be deposited into a Swiss bank account set up for occupational benefits or a lump sum cash out.</p>

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:16pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;color:#5A2D82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">2019 Proxy Statement</p></td>

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;color:#5A2D82;font-family:Arial;font-size:12pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU77"></a><a name="N2016_NONQUALIFIED_DEFERRED_COMPENSATION"></a><font style="font-weight:bold;color:#5A2D82;font-family:Arial;font-size:12pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="N2016_NONQUALIFIED_DEFERRED_COMPENSATION"></a>2018 Non-Qualified Deferr</font><font style="font-weight:bold;color:#5A2D82;font-family:Arial;font-size:12pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">ed Compensation Benefits </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:12pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#160;</p>

<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="center" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100.32%;">
<tr>
<td valign="bottom"  BGCOLOR="#683F8B" style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0.75pt;padding-Top:0.75pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:12.86%;">

<td valign="bottom"  BGCOLOR="#E6E1EE" style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0.75pt;padding-Top:0.75pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:3.2%; border-top:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-right:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(2) Amounts in this column are also included in the &#8220;All Other Compensation&#8221; column in the 2018 Summary Compensation Table. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(3) Amounts in this column are at market rates and are not reflected in the 2018 Summary Compensation Table. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(4) The aggregate balance includes amounts that were reported as compensation for our NEOs in prior years. Amounts reported attributable to base salary, AIP awards or all other compensation that were reported in the Summary Compensation Table of previously filed proxy statements for the participating NEOs are as follows: Mr.&#160;Van de Put &#8211; $0; Mr. Zaramella &#8211; $0; Mr.&#160;Gladden &#8211; $687,900; Ms. Alviti &#8211; $0; Mr.&#160;Cofer&#160;&#8211;&#160;$1,084,212; and Mr.&#160;Walter&#160;&#8211;&#160;$0. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Mondel&#275;z Global LLC Supplemental Benefits Plan I </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Because the Code limits the amount that may be contributed to our U.S. tax-qualified defined contribution plan on behalf of an employee, we offer our U.S.-based NEOs a supplemental defined contribution program under the Mondel&#275;z Global LLC Supplemental Benefits Plan I. This is an unfunded non-qualified plan that allows eligible employees to defer a portion of their annual compensation (base salary and AIP awards) and receive corresponding matching amounts to the extent that their contributions to the tax-qualified defined contribution plan (and the corresponding matching contributions) are limited by Code Sections&#160;401(a)(17) or 415. In addition, employees hired after 2008 or localized to the United States after 2015, who are not otherwise eligible to participate in the Mondel&#275;z Global LLC Retirement Plan, receive an additional non-elective Company contribution to the Mondel&#275;z Global LLC Supplemental Benefits Plan I, equal to 4.5% of eligible compensation. The timing of distributions depends on whether the amount distributed is subject to Code Section&#160;409A. For distributions not subject to Code Section&#160;409A, the distribution will be made in accordance with the employee&#8217;s distribution election. For distributions subject to Code Section&#160;409A, employees will receive their account balances in a lump sum soon after separation from service. (An employee who is a &#8220;specified employee&#8221; for purposes of Code Section 409A will have the lump sum delayed for six months.) Amounts deferred and notional employer matching contributions earn the same notional rate of return as the Income Fund, which is a market rate investment option available to participants in the U.S. tax-qualified defined contribution plan. The rate of return under this investment option in 2018 was 2.44%.</p>

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:1pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;color:#FCFCFC;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="Background-color:#5B2D83;">&#160;&#160;Executive Compensation Tables</font><font style="Background-color:#5B2B82;">&#160;&#160;</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_Hlk3895947"></a><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU78"></a><font style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Mondel</font><font style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#275;z Global LLC Executive Deferred Compensation Plan </font></p>
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The MEDCP is a non-qualified plan that allows our U.S.-based NEOs to defer, on a pre-tax basis, up to 50% of salary and up to 100% of their AIP award. The notional investment options are similar to those offered to participants in our U.S. tax-qualified defined contribution plan. An executive who elects to defer compensation must decide whether to defer receipt of the compensation until the executive&#8217;s separation from service, as determined under Code Section&#160;409A, or to receive a distribution while still employed with the Company. Distributions may be made in a lump sum or annual installments of between two and ten years. (An executive who is a &#8220;specified employee&#8221; for purposes of Code Section&#160;409A will have the distribution delayed for six months following a separation from service.) </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The notional investment options available to the executives under the MEDCP are selected by the Company and may be changed from time to time. Participants are permitted to change their investment elections at any time on a prospective basis. The table below shows the available notional investment options under the MEDCP and their annual rate of return for the calendar year ended December&#160;31, 2018. </p>

</table></div>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;color:#5A2D82;font-family:Arial;font-size:12pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="POTENTIAL_PAYMENTS_UPON_TERMINATION_OR_C"></a><a name="POTENTIAL_PAYMENTS_UPON_TERMINATION_OR_C"></a>Potential Payments Upon Termination or Change in Control </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The narrative and tables below describe the potential payments to each NEO upon certain terminations, including following a change in control. In accordance with SEC rules, all information described in this section is presented as if the triggering events occurred on December&#160;31, 2018. Mr.&#160;Gladden is not included in the tables as he ceased being an executive officer with his separation from the company effective July 31, 2018. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;line-height:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Involuntary Termination Without Cause (Non-Change in Control Event) </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;line-height:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Generally, we do not enter into ongoing agreements with our NEOs that provide for separation benefits on the NEO&#8217;s departure from the Company. However, if we involuntarily terminate an NEO without cause outside of a change in control event, we expect that in most cases the Compensation Committee would offer separation benefits as consideration for protections we would likely seek such as a release of claims and entering into non-compete, non-solicitation and confidentiality agreements. More specifically, we expect to treat our U.S. salaried NEOs (other than Mr.&#160;Van de Put) at least comparably to other U.S. salaried employees whom we involuntarily terminate without cause. For U.S. salaried employees such as our NEOs, our severance plan provides an employee whose job is eliminated with severance pay of up to 12 months based on length of service. </p>
<div>
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="center" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top"  style="width:6%;">
<p style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="width:94%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td valign="middle"  BGCOLOR="#683F8B" style="padding-Right:4pt;width:6%;">
<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:2pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#FFFFFF;font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">72</a></p></td>
<td valign="middle"  style="width:94%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:16pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;color:#5A2D82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">2019 Proxy Statement</p></td>
</tr>
</table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:1pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;color:#FCFCFC;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="Background-color:#5B2D83;">&#160;&#160;Executive Compensation Tables</font><font style="Background-color:#5B2B82;">&#160;&#160;</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;line-height:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU79"></a><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The following chart reflects the typical separation benefits that may be offered to a U.S. NEO (other than Mr.&#160;Van de Put</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(</sup></font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">1)</sup></font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">) whom we involuntarily terminate without cause. The Compensation Committee would determine actual terms and conditions based on the particular facts in a specific case. </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:12pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#160;</p>
<div>
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="center" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#EEE9F2" style="width:22.92%; border-top:solid 1pt #6B408E;">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:3.6pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Severance Benefits</p></td>
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#EEE9F2" style="width:77.08%; border-top:solid 1pt #6B408E;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:20.25pt;;text-indent:-20.25pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; CEO<sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(</sup><sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">1</sup><sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">)</sup>: 24 months of base salary.</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:13pt;;text-indent:-13pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;All other NEOs: 12 months of base salary.</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:4pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:13pt;;text-indent:-13pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Payment in a lump sum. </font></p></td>
</tr>
<tr style="height:29.85pt;">
<td valign="top"  style="width:22.92%; border-top:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:4pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:3.6pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Pension, Health and Welfare&#160;Benefits</p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="width:77.08%; border-top:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:13pt;;text-indent:-13pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;No pension crediting or continuation of health and welfare benefits coverage.</font></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#EEE9F2" style="width:22.92%;">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:3.6pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Outplacement Services</p></td>
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#EEE9F2" style="width:77.08%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:4pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:13pt;;text-indent:-13pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Outplacement services for up to 12 months.</font></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td valign="top"  style="width:22.92%;">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:3.6pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Treatment of AIP Award</p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="width:77.08%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:4pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:18pt;;text-indent:-18pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; AIP award based on actual business performance results and target individual performance.</font></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#EEE9F2" style="width:22.92%;">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:3.6pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Treatment of PSU Grants</p></td>
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#EEE9F2" style="width:77.08%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:4pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:18pt;;text-indent:-18pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Outstanding PSU grants are generally forfeited. However, our Compensation Committee may exercise discretion to vest some or all of the grants subject to actual Company performance for the full performance cycle. </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:4pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:18pt;;text-indent:-18pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Generally, for employees, including NEOs, eligible for retirement (minimum age 55 with at least ten years of service), their PSU grants prorata vest, subject to actual Company performance, based on the number of months of active employment during the applicable performance cycle.</font></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td valign="top"  style="width:22.92%;">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:3.6pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Treatment of Deferred Stock Unit&#160;Grants</p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="width:77.08%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:4pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:18pt;;text-indent:-18pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Outstanding deferred stock unit grants are generally forfeited; however, our Compensation Committee may exercise discretion to accelerate vesting of some or all of the grants. </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:4pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:18pt;;text-indent:-18pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Generally, for employees, including NEOs, eligible for retirement (minimum age 55 with at least ten years of service), their deferred stock unit grants made on or after February 22, 2016 prorata vest based on the number of months of active employment during the vesting period.</font></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#EEE9F2" style="width:22.92%; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #6B408E;">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:3.6pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Treatment of Stock Options</p></td>
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#EEE9F2" style="width:77.08%; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #6B408E;">
<p style="margin-bottom:4pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:18pt;;text-indent:-18pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Unvested stock option grants are generally forfeited; however, our Compensation Committee may exercise discretion to accelerate vesting of some or all of the grants. </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:4pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:18pt;;text-indent:-18pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Generally, for employees, including NEOs, eligible for retirement (minimum age 55 with at least ten years of service), stock option grants continue to vest under the original vesting schedule, provided the employee is actively employed for at least 90 days following the grant date.</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:4pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:18pt;;text-indent:-18pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;An individual who is eligible for retirement has the remaining full term to exercise vested options. An individual who is involuntarily terminated without cause who is not retirement eligible, has until the earlier of 12 months from termination or the end of the term to exercise vested options.</font></p></td>
</tr>
</table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(1) Per Mr.&#160;Van de Put&#8217;s offer of employment, his separation benefits will be calculated as noted below assuming he involuntarily terminates employment without cause on or before November&#160;20, 2019. If he involuntarily terminates employment without cause after November 20, 2019, he would receive 24 months of base salary as separation pay which is consistent with the severance benefits for our previous CEO. </p>

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU80"></a><font style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Potential Payout Upon an Involuntary Termination Without Cause at Fiscal Year-End 2018 </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:12pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#160;</p>
<div>

<tr>
<td valign="bottom"  BGCOLOR="#683F8B" style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0.75pt;padding-Top:0.75pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:28.54%; border-top:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-left:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="bottom"  BGCOLOR="#683F8B" style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0.75pt;padding-Top:0.75pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:0.96%; border-top:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-right:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#FFFFFF;font-size:7pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td colspan="2" valign="bottom"  BGCOLOR="#683F8B" style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0.75pt;padding-Top:0.75pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:9.82%; border-top:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-left:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-right:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#FFFFFF;font-size:7pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Separation</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#FFFFFF;font-size:7pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Pay<sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(1)</sup></p></td>
<td colspan="2" valign="bottom"  BGCOLOR="#683F8B" style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0.75pt;padding-Top:0.75pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:9.82%; border-top:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-left:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-right:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#FFFFFF;font-size:7pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Annual</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#FFFFFF;font-size:7pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Incentive</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#FFFFFF;font-size:7pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Award<sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(2)</sup></p></td>
<td colspan="2" valign="bottom"  BGCOLOR="#683F8B" style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0.75pt;padding-Top:0.75pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:9.82%; border-top:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-left:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-right:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#FFFFFF;font-size:7pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Value of</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#FFFFFF;font-size:7pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Unvested</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#FFFFFF;font-size:7pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">PSU Grants<sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(3)</sup></p></td>
<td colspan="2" valign="bottom"  BGCOLOR="#683F8B" style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0.75pt;padding-Top:0.75pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:9.82%; border-top:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-left:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-right:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#FFFFFF;font-size:7pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Value of</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#FFFFFF;font-size:7pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Unvested</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#FFFFFF;font-size:7pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Stock</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#FFFFFF;font-size:7pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Grants<sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(4)</sup></p></td>
<td colspan="2" valign="bottom"  BGCOLOR="#683F8B" style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0.75pt;padding-Top:0.75pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:9.82%; border-top:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-left:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-right:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">

<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#000000;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8211;</p></td>
<td valign="bottom"  BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0.75pt;padding-Top:0.75pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:0.96%; border-top:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-right:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#FF0000;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="bottom"  BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0.75pt;padding-Top:0.75pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:8.84%; border-top:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-left:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">
<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#000000;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8211;</p></td>
<td valign="bottom"  BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0.75pt;padding-Top:0.75pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:0.96%; border-top:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-right:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#000000;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="bottom"  BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0.75pt;padding-Top:0.75pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:10.54%; border-top:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-left:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">
<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#000000;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">12,500</p></td>
<td valign="bottom"  BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0.75pt;padding-Top:0.75pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:0.96%; border-top:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-right:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#FF0000;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="bottom"  BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0.75pt;padding-Top:0.75pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:8.84%; border-top:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-left:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">
<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#000000;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">1,264,720</p></td>
<td valign="bottom"  BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0.75pt;padding-Top:0.75pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:0.96%; border-top:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-right:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#FF0000;font-size:1pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&nbsp;</p></td>
</tr>
</table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(1) Per Mr.&#160;Van de Put&#8217;s offer of employment, the amount reflects 24 months of base salary and 24 months of target awards under our AIP. The amounts reflect 12 months of base salary for the other NEOs. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(2) Amounts reflect 2018 AIP awards assuming target individual performance and the final corporate rating of 134% for all NEOs except Mr. Walter; reflects final North America rating of 76% for Mr. Walter. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(3) Per the terms of the grants made to Mr.&#160;Van de Put in connection with his offer of employment, amount reflects the full value, assuming target performance, of his PSU grants received at the time of his commencement of employment. The PSUs earned are based on actual Company performance during their respective performance cycles. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_Hlk1380206"></a><a name="_Hlk1380206"></a>(4) Per the terms of the grants made to Mr.&#160;Van de Put in connection with his offer of employment, amounts reflect the value of his outstanding unvested deferred stock units and stock options received at the time of his commencement of employment. Per the terms of the grants made to Ms. Alviti in connection with her offer of employment, amounts reflect the value of her outstanding unvested deferred stock units. All amounts are based on a December&#160;31, 2018 closing stock price of $40.03. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Double Trigger Change in Control Arrangements </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">NEOs are not eligible for any benefit solely upon a change in control. Our CIC Plan for senior executive officers, including the NEOs, provides for certain benefits upon an involuntary termination of employment without &#8220;Cause&#8221; or voluntary termination for &#8220;Good Reason&#8221; within two years following a change in control. To receive any benefits under the CIC Plan, a participant must abide by certain restrictive covenants, including a non-compete and non-solicitation for one year following termination. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Additionally, the Equity Plan also provides for the treatment of unassumed outstanding equity grants following a change in control and assumed outstanding equity grants upon an involuntary termination of employment without Cause or voluntary termination for Good Reason within two years following a change in control. </p>
<div>
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="center" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">

<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:2pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#FFFFFF;font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">74</a></p></td>
<td valign="middle"  style="width:94%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:16pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;color:#5A2D82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">2019 Proxy Statement</p></td>
