<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:1pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;color:#FCFCFC;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="Background-color:#5B2D83;">&#160;&#160;Executive Compensation Tables</font><font style="Background-color:#5B2B82;">&#160;&#160;</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU81"></a><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The key elements of the CIC Plan and Equity Plan assuming a double trigger event are described in the table below. </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:12pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#160;</p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr style="height:14.4pt;">
<td valign="bottom"  style="width:26.66%; border-bottom:solid 1pt #5B2B82;">
<p style="margin-bottom:1pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:3.6pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#5A2D82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Plan Element</p></td>
<td valign="bottom"  style="padding-left:7.2pt;padding-Right:0pt;padding-Top:0pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:73.34%; border-bottom:solid 1pt #5B2B82;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:-7.2pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#5A2D82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Description</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#EEE9F2" style="width:26.66%; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:3.6pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Definition of Change in <br />Control</p></td>
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#EEE9F2" style="width:73.34%; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Subject to certain exceptions, the occurrence of one of the conditions below:</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:12.95pt;;text-indent:-12.95pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Acquisition of 20% or more of our outstanding voting securities;</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:18pt;;text-indent:-18pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Changes to Board membership during any consecutive 24-month period that results in less than 50% of the current Board members elected to the Board;</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:18pt;;text-indent:-18pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;After the reorganization, merger, statutory share exchange or consolidation or any other material transaction involving the Company or any of our subsidiaries, over 50% of outstanding voting securities are not owned by Company shareholders; or</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:18pt;;text-indent:-18pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Complete liquidation of Mondel&#275;z International or the sale of all or substantially all of our assets.</font></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td valign="top"  style="width:26.66%; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:3.6pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Definition of &#8220;Cause&#8221;</p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="width:73.34%; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:13pt;;text-indent:-13pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Subject to <font style="color:#000000;">certain exceptions, the occurrence of one of the conditions below:</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:18pt;;text-indent:-18pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Continued failure to substantially perform the participant&#8217;s job duties (other than resulting from incapacity due to disability);</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:18pt;;text-indent:-18pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Gross negligence, dishonesty or violation of any reasonable rule or regulation of the Company where the violation results in significant damage to the Company; or</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:4pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:18pt;;text-indent:-18pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Engaging in other conduct which adversely reflects on Company in any material respect.</font></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#EEE9F2" style="width:26.66%; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:3.6pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Definition of &#8220;Good <br />Reason&#8221;</p></td>
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#EEE9F2" style="width:73.34%; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:13pt;;text-indent:-13pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Material reduction in job duties;</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:13pt;;text-indent:-13pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Material reduction in compensation;</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:13pt;;text-indent:-13pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Relocation beyond 50 miles; or</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:4pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:13pt;;text-indent:-13pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Failure to assume the obligations under the CIC Plan or Equity Plan.</font></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td valign="top"  style="width:26.66%; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:3.6pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Severance and Benefits <br />Amounts</p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="width:73.34%; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:18pt;;text-indent:-18pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;CEO: 2.99 times base salary plus target annual incentive payable by the Company in a lump sum;</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:18pt;;text-indent:-18pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;All other NEOs: two times base salary plus target annual incentive payable by the Company in a lump sum;</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:18pt;;text-indent:-18pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Additional credited years of pension service (if applicable) and welfare benefits equal to three years for the CEO and two years for the other NEOs;</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:18pt;;text-indent:-18pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Continuation of financial counseling and car allowances for three years for the CEO and two years for the other NEOs; and</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:4pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:13pt;;text-indent:-13pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Outplacement services up to two years following the termination.</font></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#EEE9F2" style="width:26.66%; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:3.6pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Treatment of AIP Awards <br />and PSU Grants</p></td>
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#EEE9F2" style="width:73.34%; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:4pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:18pt;;text-indent:-18pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;NEO is eligible to receive prorated cash payments (for service during the performance cycle) representing both the award under the AIP and outstanding PSU grants. In the case of outstanding PSUs, if at least fifty percent of the performance cycle has elapsed, cash payment would be calculated using the target level of PSUs (no proration). PSU value is calculated by multiplying the number of shares by the closing stock price on the last trading date preceding the date of CIC.</font></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td valign="top"  style="width:26.66%; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:4pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:3.6pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Treatment of Equity Grants</p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="width:73.34%; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:4pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:18pt;;text-indent:-18pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Deferred stock units and unvested stock option grants vest. Participants have the full-term to exercise all stock options, including those previously vested.</font></p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#EEE9F2" style="width:26.66%; border-bottom:solid 1pt #5B2B82;">
<p style="margin-bottom:4pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:3.6pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Maximum CIC Plan <br />Benefit/No Gross Up for Payment of Excise Tax</p></td>
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#EEE9F2" style="width:73.34%; border-bottom:solid 1pt #5B2B82;">
<p style="margin-bottom:4pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:18pt;;text-indent:-18pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;The maximum benefit under the CIC Plan or otherwise is the greater of the full benefit or a reduced benefit that does not trigger the excise tax under Code Section 4999 as determined on an after-tax basis for each.</font></p></td>
</tr>

<td valign="bottom"  BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0.75pt;padding-Top:0.75pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:0.9%; border-top:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-bottom:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF; border-right:solid 0.75pt #BFBFBF;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#000000;font-size:1pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&nbsp;</p></td>

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:6pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#160;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(1) Amounts reflect 2.99 times base salary plus target annual incentive for Mr. Van de Put and two times base salary plus target annual incentive for all other NEOs.<font style="color:#000000;"> </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(2) Amounts reflect target awards under our 2018 AIP. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_Hlk1382799"></a><a name="_Hlk1382799"></a>(3) Amounts reflect target PSU grants for the 2016-2018 and 2017-2019 performance cycles, as well as prorated target PSU grants for the 2018-2020 performance cycle. Per the terms of the grants made to Mr.&#160;Van de Put in connection with his offer of employment, his amount also reflects the full value, assuming target performance, of his PSU grants received at the time of his commencement of employment. All amounts are based on a December&#160;31, 2018 closing stock price of $40.03. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(4) Amounts reflect the value of immediate vesting of all outstanding unvested deferred stock unit grants and outstanding unvested stock options. All amounts are based on a December&#160;31, 2018 closing stock price of $40.03. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(5) Amounts reflect our cost for providing medical, dental, vision, long-term disability and life insurance premiums for three years for Mr.&#160;Van de Put and two years for all other NEOs. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(6) Amounts reflect the value for continuation of the financial counseling allowance (three years for Mr.&#160;Van de Put valued at $30,000 and two years for all other NEOs valued at $15,000), car allowance (three years for Mr.&#160;Van de Put valued at $69,999 and two years for all other NEOs valued at $30,000) and outplacement services (two years valued at $25,000). </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(7) Amount reflects an additional two years of pension accrual for Mr.&#160;Cofer. Mr.&#160;Van de Put, Mr. Zaramella, Ms. Alviti and Mr.&#160;Walter are not currently pension eligible. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Potential Payout Upon Other Types of Separations </p>
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Death or Disability<font style="font-style:normal;">. If an NEO terminates employment due to death or disability, all of the NEO&#8217;s outstanding unvested deferred stock units and stock option grants would vest. In addition, the NEO (or beneficiary) would become eligible for an award under the AIP and a prorated award for outstanding PSU grants. </font></p>
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The table below describes the estimated value of such payments based on a December&#160;31, 2018 termination due to death or disability. </p>

Per the terms of the grants made to Mr.&#160;Van de Put in connection with his offer of employment, his amount also reflects the full value, assuming target performance, of his PSU grants received at the time of his commencement of employment. All amounts are based on a December&#160;31, 2018 closing stock price of $40.03. </p>

All amounts are based on a December&#160;31, 2018 closing stock price of $40.03. </p>

<div>
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="center" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td style="width:100%;"></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#E6E1EE">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:12.25pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#5B2B82;font-size:16pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="HUMAN_RESOURCES_COMPENSATION"></a><a name="HUMAN_RESOURCES_COMPENSATION"></a>Human Resources and Compensation Committee Report for the Year Ended December&#160;31, 2018 </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:12.2pt;;margin-right:2.22%;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Compensation Committee oversees the compensation programs on behalf of the Board. In fulfilling its oversight responsibilities, the Compensation Committee reviewed and discussed with management the Compensation Discussion and Analysis included in this Proxy Statement. Based on that review and discussion, the Compensation Committee recommended that the Board include the Compensation Discussion and Analysis in the Proxy Statement to be filed with the SEC in connection with the Annual Meeting and incorporate it by reference in the Annual Report on Form 10-K for the year ended December&#160;31, 2018, filed with the SEC on February&#160;8, 2019. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:12.2pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Human Resources and Compensation Committee: </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:12.2pt;;margin-right:2.22%;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Lois D. Juliber, Chair </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:12.2pt;;margin-right:2.22%;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Lewis W.K. Booth </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:12.2pt;;margin-right:2.22%;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Charles E. Bunch </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:12.2pt;;margin-right:2.22%;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Mark D. Ketchum </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:12.2pt;;margin-right:2.22%;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Peter W. May</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:12.25pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Jean-Fran&#231;ois M. L. van Boxmeer </p></td>
</tr>
</table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:3.33%;text-indent:-3.33%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:9pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;color:#5A2D82;font-size:16pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="CEO_PAY_RATIO"></a><a name="CEO_PAY_RATIO"></a>CEO Pay Ratio </p>
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Our CEO to median employee pay ratio was calculated in accordance with Item 402(u) of Regulation S-K and represents a reasonable estimate. We identified our median employee (&#8220;Median Employee&#8221;) using 2018 base salaries, our consistently applied compensation measure, for all individuals who were employed by us on October&#160;1, 2018, excluding our CEO, annualized for any employees who joined the Company during 2018. </p>
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">To identify the compensation of our Median Employee, we determined the annual base salary for each of our 95,545 full-time, part-time, temporary and seasonal employees without applying any cost-of-living adjustments. We excluded 2,017 employees in Venezuela from our calculation as we do not report Venezuela in our consolidated financials. For an employee paid in a currency other than U.S. dollars, we converted annual base salaries into U.S. dollars. We then applied the <font style="font-style:italic;">de minimis</font> exemption excluding 4,738<font style="font-size:12pt;"><sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(1)</sup> </font>non-U.S. employees who represented less than 5% of our population. After applying this exemption, we used base salary information for 90,807 of our employees. </p>
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Based on this data and process, we determined that our Median Employee was a part-time hourly employee with annual total compensation of $30,639. This is the same employee we used for the 2017 CEO Pay Ratio calculation. The 2018 compensation for this employee is lower than in 2017 because the 2018 pension value is lower than the amount calculated in 2017, primarily due to increased interest rates, despite an additional year of accrued benefit service. The annual total compensation for Dirk Van de Put, our CEO, as reported in the Summary Compensation Table was $14,969,900 which reflects compensation received for the full calendar year. Therefore, the ratio of our CEO&#8217;s annual total compensation to the Median Employee&#8217;s annual total compensation was 489 to 1. </p>
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Median employee compensation reflects that eight out of ten employees are located outside the U.S. and significant use of part-time and seasonal employees throughout the year. As a global company that generates more than 75% of our sales internationally, our employees are located in more than 80 countries with a heavy presence in emerging markets. Five of our top six largest employee populations are in emerging market countries. Furthermore, over 62% of our workforce consists of hourly employees. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:1pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;color:#5A2D82;font-size:16pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="OWNERSHIP_EQUITY_SECURITIES"></a><a name="OWNERSHIP_EQUITY_SECURITIES"></a>Ownership of Equity Securities </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The following table shows the number of shares of Common Stock beneficially owned as of March&#160;12, 2019, unless otherwise noted, by each director and NEO, as well as the number of shares beneficially owned by all of our current directors and executive officers as a group. None of the Common Stock owned by these individuals is subject to any pledge. Unless otherwise indicated, each of the named individuals has sole voting and investment power with respect to the shares shown. </p>

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(1) Includes stock options that are exercisable or will become exercisable within 60 days after March&#160;12, 2019 as follows: Ms. Alviti &#8211; 0; Mr.&#160;Cofer&#160;&#8211;513,006; Mr. Van de Put&#160;&#8211;&#160;173,492; Mr. Walter&#160;&#8211;&#160;19,912; Mr.&#160;Zaramella&#160;&#8211;&#160;121,771; and all other executive officers&#160;&#8211; 1,111,513. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(2) Includes deferred stock units granted under the 2006 Stock Compensation Plan for Non-Employee Directors and the Equity Plan. For a description of these deferred stock units, see &#8220;Compensation of Non-Employee Directors&#8221; above. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(3) Based on 1,445,747,721 issued and outstanding shares of our Common Stock as of March&#160;12, 2019. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(4) Includes grants of 5,534 deferred stock units to Mr.&#160;May under the Equity Plan and 18,819,336 shares owned by certain funds and investment vehicles (collectively, the &#8220;Trian Entities&#8221;) managed by Trian Fund Management, L.P. (&#8220;Trian&#8221;), an institutional investment manager located at 280 Park Avenue, 41st Floor, New York, NY 10017. Trian determines the investment and voting decisions of the Trian Entities with respect to the shares of the company held by them. None of the 18,819,336 shares are held directly by Mr.&#160;May. Substantially all of these shares are currently held in the ordinary course of business with other investment securities owned by the Trian Entities in co-mingled margin accounts with a prime broker, which prime broker may, from time to time, extend margin credit to certain Trian Entities, subject to applicable federal margin regulations, stock exchange rules and credit policies. Mr.&#160;May is a member of Trian Fund Management GP, LLC, which is the general partner of Trian, and therefore is in a position to determine the investment and voting decisions made by Trian on behalf of the Trian Entities. Accordingly, Mr.&#160;May may be deemed to indirectly beneficially own (as that term is defined in Rule 13d-3 under the Exchange Act) the shares owned by the Trian Entities. Mr.&#160;May disclaims beneficial ownership of such shares for all other purposes. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(5) This group includes, in addition to the individuals named in the table, Maurizio Brusadelli,<font style="font-size:9.5pt;"> </font>Vinzenz P. Gruber, Robin S. Hargrove, Alejandro R. Lorenzo, Daniel P. Myers and Gerhard W. Pleuhs.</p>

<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;color:#000000;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">7.4</p></td>
</tr>
</table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(1) Based on the Schedule 13G/A filed by BlackRock, Inc. on February 6, 2019 with the SEC. The Schedule 13G/A discloses that BlackRock, Inc., in its capacity as the parent holding company of certain subsidiaries, had sole voting power over 77,947,796 shares and sole dispositive power over 90,450,969 shares and shared voting and dispositive power over 0 shares.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(2) Based on the Schedule 13G/A filed by The Vanguard Group on February&#160;11, 2019 with the SEC. The Schedule 13G/A discloses that The Vanguard Group, as investment advisor, had sole voting power over 1,681,936 shares, shared voting power over 386,467 shares, sole dispositive power over 105,581,972 shares and shared dispositive power over 2,039,507 shares. </p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;color:#5A2D82;font-family:Arial;font-size:12pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="SECTION_16A_BENEFICIAL_OWNERSHIP_REPORTI"></a><a name="SECTION_16A_BENEFICIAL_OWNERSHIP_REPORTI"></a>Section&#160;16(a) Beneficial Ownership Reporting Compliance </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Section&#160;16(a) of the Exchange Act requires executive officers, directors and persons who beneficially own more than 10% of our Common Stock to report to the SEC their ownership of Common Stock and changes in that ownership. We reviewed copies of reports filed pursuant to Section&#160;16(a) of the Exchange Act and written representations from the applicable reporting persons. Based solely on that review, we believe that for the fiscal year ended December&#160;31, 2018, all required reports under Section&#160;16(a) were filed on a timely basis.</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:3.33%;text-indent:-3.33%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:1pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<td valign="middle"  style="width:94%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:16pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;color:#5A2D82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">2019 Proxy Statement</p></td>

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:1pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;color:#5A2D82;font-size:16pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="toc498940_52"></a><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU86"></a><a name="ITEM_3_ADVISORY_VOTE_TO_APPROVE_EXECUTIV"></a><font style="color:#5A2D82;font-size:16pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="ITEM_3_ADVISORY_VOTE_TO_APPROVE_EXECUTIV"></a>ITEM&#160;2. Advisory Vote to App</font><font style="color:#5A2D82;font-size:16pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">rove Executive Compensation</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">In accordance with the Dodd-Frank Wall Street Reform and Consumer Protection Act of 2010 and related SEC rules, and consistent with our shareholders&#8217; preference (as indicated by vote at our 2017 Annual Meeting), the Board adopted a policy of providing shareholders an annual vote to approve, on an advisory (non-binding) basis, the compensation of our NEOs (commonly known as a &#8220;say-on-pay&#8221; vote). </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Our executives&#160;&#8211;&#160;including our NEOs&#160;&#8211;&#160;are critical to our success. That is why we design our executive compensation programs to attract, retain and motivate superior executive talent. At the same time, we structure our executive compensation programs to focus on shareholders&#8217; interests by incenting superior sustainable long-term performance. Under our executive compensation programs, we align pay and performance by making a significant portion of our NEOs&#8217; compensation contingent on: </p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">reaching specific annual and long-term performance measures; and </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">increasing shareholder value. </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We also have strong compensation-related design and governance practices to protect our shareholders&#8217; interests. Shareholders can find more information about these practices under &#8220;Board Committees and Membership&#160;&#8211;&#160;Human Resources and Compensation Committee&#8221; and &#8220;Compensation Discussion and Analysis.&#8221; These practices include: </p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">substantial stock ownership and stock holding requirements for directors and executive officers which includes a minimum one-year hold on all shares received through the vesting of performance share units or deferred stock units, or the exercise of stock options; </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">a long-term incentive program that is 100% equity-based with our executives&#8217; entire annual equity grant aligned with shareholders as 75% of our executives&#8217; annual equity grant is in the form of performance share units and 25% is in the form of stock options; </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">

<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">88% of our CEO&#8217;s target total compensation being at-risk incentive-based pay, of which 71% is based on long-term performance; </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">

<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">

<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">setting both CEO and NEO target total compensation at or below the median of the compensation survey peer group; </p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">

<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">Cash provided by operating activities was $3.9 billion; Free Cash Flow<sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(1)</sup> was $2.9 billion</p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:11.67%;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We announced an 18% dividend per share increase in the third quarter of 2018 and returned $3.4&#160;billion of capital to shareholders while continuing to invest in our business. <font style="color:#000000;">In September 2018, we also unveiled </font>our new strategy to position us to lead the snacking industry. <font style="color:#000000;">Our results demonstrate the power of our brands, the strength of our global footprint and the potential of our strategic plan. </font></p>
<div align="left"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:20%;"><tr><td style="width:20%;"></td></tr><tr><td valign="top"  style="border-bottom:Solid 1pt #000000;"><p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;text-indent:0pt;font-size:8pt;">&nbsp;</p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:0%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(1)</sup></font><font style="font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> See definition and </font><font style="font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">GAAP to non-GAAP reconciliation in Annex A</font><font style="font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">. </font></p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"></p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:1pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<div>
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="center" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top"  style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0pt;padding-Top:0pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:94%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>

<td valign="middle"  style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0pt;padding-Top:0pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:94%;">
<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;margin-right:2.96%;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:16pt;font-family:Calibri;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><img src="gycirsmwh4vw000013.jpg" title="" alt="" style="width:85px;height:20px;"></p></td>
<td valign="middle"  BGCOLOR="#683F8B" style="padding-left:4pt;padding-Right:0pt;padding-Top:0pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:6%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:2pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#FFFFFF;font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">81</a></p></td>
</tr>
</table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:1pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;color:#FCFCFC;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;letter-spacing:-0.15pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="Background-color:#5B2D83;">&#160;ITEM 2. Advisory Vote to Approve Executive Compensation&#160;&#160;</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU87"></a><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We were very disappointed with the 2018 say-on-pay vote and as a result the Compensation Committee took decisive steps to respond to that vote. </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We engaged further with shareholders to better understand the reasons for the substantial decrease in support and the changes necessary to regain the support of our shareholders. </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">After extensive shareholder outreach, we learned that the primary concerns in 2017 were related to one-time compensation actions taken in connection with the CEO succession and transition. Although shareholders we spoke with generally believed our ongoing compensation programs were aligned with a pay-for-performance culture, we made several changes to our executive compensation program in both 2018 and 2019 to further enhance our pay-for-performance culture and support our new strategy. These changes included program design changes in the annual incentive plan and performance metrics changes in both the annual and long-term incentive programs. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We encourage you to read the &#8220;Compensation Discussion and Analysis&#8221; beginning on page 39 and the &#8220;Executive Compensation Tables&#8221; beginning on page 63 to better understand the details around our shareholder outreach, changes made to our incentive programs and how our 2018 pay aligned with 2018 performance. In addition, in 2018 we appointed a new CFO and hired a new CHRO. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Compensation Committee and the Board believe that our executive compensation programs serve our shareholders&#8217; interests and we will continue to refine our compensation programs to align compensation with the Company&#8217;s business and talent strategies as well as the long-term interests of shareholders. Accordingly, we ask you to vote &#8220;FOR&#8221; the following resolution at our annual meeting:</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;margin-left:4.54%;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8220;RESOLVED, that Mondel&#275;z International&#8217;s shareholders approve, on an advisory basis, the compensation paid to Mondel&#275;z International&#8217;s NEOs, as disclosed in this Proxy Statement pursuant to the SEC&#8217;s compensation disclosure rules, including the Compensation Discussion and Analysis, the Executive Compensation Tables and related narrative discussion.&#8221; </p>
<p style="margin-top:6pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">While the say-on-pay vote is advisory and therefore, not binding on Mondel&#275;z International, the Compensation Committee or the Board, the Board and Compensation Committee value the opinions of our shareholders. We carefully and thoughtfully consider our shareholders&#8217; concerns and opinions in evaluating our executive compensation program. <font style="color:#000000;">We believe the compensation paid to our named executive officers for 2018 appropriately reflects and rewards their contribution to our performance and that the changes we have made to our compensation programs are responsive to shareholder feedback and our strategic goals. </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">If a significant percentage of our shareholders vote against NEO compensation, we will consider our shareholders&#8217; concerns and the Compensation Committee will evaluate whether any actions are necessary or appropriate to address those concerns. Unless the Board modifies its policy of holding an advisory say-on-pay vote on an annual basis, the next advisory say-on-pay vote will be held at our 2020 Annual Meeting of Shareholders. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">THE BOARD RECOMMENDS A VOTE FOR THE APPROVAL OF OUR EXECUTIVE COMPENSATION. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="width:94%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>

<td valign="middle"  BGCOLOR="#683F8B" style="padding-Right:4pt;width:6%;">
<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:2pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#FFFFFF;font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">82</a></p></td>
<td valign="middle"  style="width:94%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:16pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;color:#5A2D82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">2019 Proxy Statement</p></td>
</tr>
</table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:1pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;color:#5A2D82;font-size:16pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU88"></a><a name="ITEM_2_RATIFICATION__SELECTION_INDEPENDE"></a><font style="color:#5A2D82;font-size:16pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="ITEM_2_RATIFICATION__SELECTION_INDEPENDE"></a>ITEM&#160;3. Ratification of the Selection of Independent</font><font style="color:#5A2D82;font-size:16pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> Registered Public Accountants for Fiscal Year 2019 </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Audit Committee is directly responsible for the selection, appointment, compensation, retention, oversight and termination of the independent registered public accountants. PricewaterhouseCoopers LLP has been the Company&#8217;s independent registered public accountants <font style="color:#000000;">since 2001. </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Review of Independent Registered Public Accountants </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Audit Committee annually reviews the performance of its independent registered public accountants and considers whether to reappoint the firm for the following year or appoint a different firm. In determining which firm to appoint as the Company&#8217;s independent registered public accountants for 2019, the Audit Committee considered numerous factors, including: </p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:6.67%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:12pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-family:Arial;font-size:12pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-family:Arial;font-size:12pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:12pt;"><font style="font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">firm capabilities, approach and fees; </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
