<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">7.</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">I am a participant in the Altria Deferred Profit Sharing Plan for Hourly Employees, the Altria Deferred Profit Sharing Plan for Salaried Employees, the Philip Morris International Deferred Profit-Sharing Plan or the Miller Coors LLC Employees Retirement&#160;&amp; Savings Plan and have investments in the Mondel&#275;z International Stock Fund(s). Can I vote? If so, how do I vote? </p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Yes, you are entitled to vote. Your proxy card or control number for voting electronically includes all shares allocated to your Mondel&#275;z International Stock Fund account(s). With regard to each plan in which you hold the stock, your vote directs the plan trustee how to vote the shares allocated to your Mondel&#275;z International Stock Fund account(s). </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;letter-spacing:-0.15pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">In order to direct the plan trustee how to vote the shares held in your Mondel&#275;z International Stock Fund account(s), you must vote these plan shares (whether by Internet, QR code, telephone or mailed proxy card) by 11:59 p.m. EDT <font style="color:#000000;">on May&#160;10, 2019</font>. If the trustee(s) does not receive your voting instructions or proxy card by that time, the trustee(s) will vote the shares allocated to your account(s) in the same proportion as the respective plan shares for which the trustee timely received voting instructions, unless doing so would be contrary to the Employee Retirement Income Security Act of 1974. Please follow the instructions for registered shareholders described in Question 12 below to cast your vote. Note that although you may attend the Annual Meeting, you may not vote shares held in your Mondel&#275;z International Stock Fund account(s) at the Annual Meeting. </p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">8.</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">How do I vote if I participate in Mondel&#275;z International&#8217;s Direct Purchase Plan? </p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">If you hold shares in the Direct Purchase Plan, follow the instructions for registered shareholders described in Question 12 below to vote your shares. When you vote those shares, you will be voting all the shares you hold at our transfer agent as a registered shareholder. <font style="text-decoration:underline;">If you do not vote your shares, they will not be voted. PLEASE VOTE</font>. </p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">9.</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">I hold CREST Depository Interests (&#8220;CDIs&#8221;) that represent entitlements to shares of Common Stock as a result of Mondel&#275;z International&#8217;s acquisition of Cadbury in 2010. Can I vote the shares of Common Stock underlying my CDIs? If so, how do I vote? </p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Computershare Investor Services Plc (&#8220;Computershare&#8221;) will send all CREST Participants (including nominee companies and sponsored individuals) that hold CDIs a notice and Form of Proxy that allow these participants to attend and vote at the Annual Meeting. If you hold your CDIs in CREST, you can vote the underlying shares by completing and sending the Form of Proxy to the Voting Agent, Computershare, or via CREST as detailed on the Form of Proxy. Computershare must receive your vote <font style="text-decoration:underline;">by 3:00 p.m. London </font><font style="text-decoration:underline;color:#000000;">time on May&#160;9, 2019</font><font style="color:#000000;">. C</font>omputershare will then notify the Registrar of the vote for the underlying shares and your vote will be included in the final tally for the Annual Meeting. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU96"></a>If Computershare holds your CDIs on your behalf within Mondel&#275;z International Corporate Sponsored Nominee Service<font style="font-style:normal;">, Computershare, as the international nominee for your CDIs, will send you a notice and Form of Direction. You may direct Computershare how to vote your underlying shares via the Internet or by returning your Form of Direction according to the </font></p>
<div>
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="center" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top"  style="width:6%;">
<p style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="width:94%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td valign="middle"  BGCOLOR="#683F8B" style="padding-Right:4pt;width:6%;">
<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:2pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#FFFFFF;font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">90</p></td>
<td valign="middle"  style="width:94%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:16pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;color:#5A2D82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">2019 Proxy Statement</p></td>
</tr>
</table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:1pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;color:#FCFCFC;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="Background-color:#5B2D83;">&#160;&#160;Frequently Asked Questions About the Annual Meeting and Voting</font><font style="Background-color:#5B2B82;">&#160;&#160;</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-style:normal;">instructions in the notice and Form of Direction </font><font style="text-decoration:underline;font-style:normal;">by 3:00 p.m. London time </font><font style="text-decoration:underline;color:#000000;font-style:normal;">on May&#160;8, 2019</font><font style="color:#000000;font-style:normal;">. Computershare </font><font style="font-style:normal;">will then arrange to vote your underlying shares according to your instructions. If you would like to attend and vote in person at the Annual Meeting, please inform Computershare, which will provide you with a letter of representation with respect to your CDIs that will enable you to attend and vote your underlying shares at the Annual Meeting on Computershare&#8217;s behalf. </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">If another international nominee holds your CDIs on your behalf<font style="font-style:normal;">, your nominee may have its own arrangements in place to provide you with a separate notice of the Annual Meeting and proxy voting card with respect to your underlying shares. In that case, please follow your nominee&#8217;s voting instructions in that notice and proxy voting card to direct your nominee how to vote your underlying shares. Please vote by the deadline stated on the nominee&#8217;s notice and proxy voting card. </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">If you hold CDIs and have questions about voting your shares of Common Stock underlying your CDIs, please contact Computershare at +44 (0)344 472 6005. </p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">10.</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">May I change or revoke my vote? </p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Yes. </p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:9.94%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">If you are a </font><font style="font-style:italic;color:#000000;">registered shareholder</font><font style="color:#000000;">, any subsequent vote you cast will replace your earlier vote. This applies whether you vote by mailing a proxy card or via QR barcode, telephone or the Internet. You may also revoke an earlier vote by voting in person at the Annual Meeting. Alternatively, you may revoke your proxy by submitting a written revocation to the Corporate Secretary at Mondel&#275;z International, Inc., Three Parkway North, Deerfield, Illinois 60015. </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:9.94%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">If you are a </font><font style="font-style:italic;color:#000000;">beneficial shareholder</font><font style="color:#000000;">, you must contact your broker, bank or other nominee for specific instructions on how to change or revoke your vote. </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">11.</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">What is the quorum requirement for the Annual Meeting? </p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">A quorum of shareholders is necessary to validly hold the Annual Meeting. A quorum will be present if a majority of the outstanding shares of Common Stock entitled to vote as of the Record Date is represented at the Annual Meeting, either in person or by proxy. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Abstentions and broker non-votes (described in Question 15 below) will be counted for the purpose of determining whether a quorum is present for the Annual Meeting. </p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">12.</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">How do I vote my shares? </p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">If you are a <font style="font-style:italic;">registered shareholder</font>, you may vote any of these four ways: </p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">

<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-family:Arial;">via the Internet at </font><font style="font-style:italic;text-decoration:underline;font-family:Arial;">www.proxyvote.com</font><font style="font-family:Arial;"> or scan the QR barcode provided (</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:Arial;">control number is required). The Internet voting system will be available 24 hours a day until 11:59 p.m. EDT on May&#160;14, 2019; </font></p></td></tr></table></div>

Call 1-800-690-6903 (toll-free) from a touch-tone telephone. The telephone voting system will be available 24 hours a day until 11:59 p.m. EDT on May&#160;14, 2019; </p></td></tr></table></div>

We must <font style="color:#000000;">receive your proxy card before the polls close at the Annual Meeting on May&#160;15, 2019; or </font></p></td></tr></table></div>

<td valign="middle"  style="padding-left:0pt;padding-Right:0pt;padding-Top:0pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:94%;">
<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;margin-right:2.96%;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:16pt;font-family:Calibri;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><img src="gycirsmwh4vw000013.jpg" title="" alt="" style="width:85px;height:20px;"></p></td>
<td valign="middle"  BGCOLOR="#683F8B" style="padding-left:4pt;padding-Right:0pt;padding-Top:0pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:6%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:2pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#FFFFFF;font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">91</a></p></td>
</tr>
</table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:1pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;color:#FCFCFC;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="Background-color:#5B2D83;">&#160;&#160;Frequently Asked Questions About the Annual Meeting and Voting</font><font style="Background-color:#5B2B82;">&#160;&#160;</font></p>
<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">13.</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU97"></a><font style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"></font><font style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">What vote is needed to elect directors? </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">To be elected in an uncontested election such as at this Annual Meeting, a director nominee must receive a majority of the votes cast&#160;&#8211;&#160;i.e., more votes FOR than AGAINST. Abstentions and broker non-votes (described in Question 15 below) are not considered as votes cast and will have no effect on the vote outcome for these matters. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">In an uncontested election, if an incumbent director nominated for re-election receives a greater number of votes AGAINST than votes FOR, the director must tender his or her resignation to the Governance Committee for its consideration following certification of the election results. The Governance Committee then will recommend to the Board whether to accept the resignation. The director will continue to serve until the Board decides whether to accept the resignation, but will not participate in the committee&#8217;s recommendation or the Board&#8217;s action regarding whether to accept the resignation offer. The Board considers all factors it deems relevant to the Company&#8217;s best interests and will publicly disclose its decision and rationale within 90 days after certification of the election results. If the Board does not accept the director&#8217;s resignation, the director will continue to serve until the next annual meeting of shareholders or until the director&#8217;s successor is duly elected and qualified. </p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">14.</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">What vote is needed to approve the other proposals? </p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;letter-spacing:-0.1pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Approval of each of Item&#160;2 (Advisory Vote to Approve Executive Compensation), Item&#160;3 (Ratification of the Selection of the Independent Registered Public Accountants), and Items 4 and 5 (Shareholder Proposals) also requires a majority of votes cast&#160;&#8211;&#160;i.e., more votes FOR than AGAINST. Abstentions and broker non-votes (described in Question 15 below) are not considered as votes cast and will have no effect on the vote outcome for Items 2, 4 and 5. There should be no broker non-votes with respect to Item&#160;3 because this is a routine matter under stock exchange rules (described in Question 15 below). </p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">15.</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">What are broker non-votes? </p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">If you are a beneficial shareholder, your vote instructs your broker, bank or other nominee, as the holder of record, how to vote your shares. Under stock exchange rules, if you do not provide voting instructions to your broker, bank or other nominee, your nominee has discretion to vote your shares only on matters classified as &#8220;routine&#8221; under stock exchange rules. The ratification of the selection of the independent registered public accountants (Item 3) is the only item on the agenda for the Annual Meeting that is routine under stock exchange rules. If you do not provide voting instructions to your broker or other nominee, your nominee may vote your shares only on Item&#160;3. In that case, your shares will count toward the quorum for the Annual Meeting and be voted on Item&#160;3, but they will not be voted on Items 1, 2, 4 and 5 and any other matters that may come to vote at the Annual Meeting, resulting in &#8220;broker non-votes&#8221; in an amount equivalent to your shares with respect to these items. </p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">16.</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">Who bears the cost of soliciting votes for the Annual Meeting? </p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Company bears the cost of soliciting your vote. The Company&#8217;s directors, officers or employees may solicit proxies or votes in person, by telephone or by electronic communication. They will not receive any additional compensation for these solicitation activities. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Company will enlist the help of banks, brokers and other nominee holders in soliciting proxies for the Annual Meeting from their customers (i.e., beneficial shareholders) and reimburse those firms for related out-of-pocket expenses. We retained Mackenzie Partners, Inc. to aid in soliciting votes for the Annual Meeting for a fee not to exceed $25,000 plus reasonable expenses. </p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">17.</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">What is Householding? </p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;letter-spacing:-0.1pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We have adopted &#8220;householding&#8221; procedures that allow us to deliver proxy materials more cost-effectively. If you are a beneficial shareholder and you and other residents at your mailing address share the same last name and also own shares of Common Stock in an account at the same broker, bank or other nominee, your nominee delivered a single Notice or set of proxy materials to your address. This method of delivery is known as householding. Householding reduces the number of mailings you receive, saves on printing and postage costs and helps the environment. Shareholders participating in householding continue to receive separate proxy cards and control numbers for voting electronically. </p>
<div>
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="center" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top"  style="width:6%;">
<p style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="width:94%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td valign="middle"  BGCOLOR="#683F8B" style="padding-Right:4pt;width:6%;">
<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:2pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#FFFFFF;font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">92</a></p></td>
<td valign="middle"  style="width:94%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:16pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;color:#5A2D82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">2019 Proxy Statement</p></td>
</tr>
</table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:1pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;color:#FCFCFC;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="Background-color:#5B2D83;">&#160;&#160;Frequently Asked Questions About the Annual Meeting and Voting</font><font style="Background-color:#5B2B82;">&#160;&#160;</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU98"></a><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">A shareholder who received a single Notice or set of proxy materials to a shared address may request a separate copy of the Notice or proxy materials be sent to him or her by contacting in writing Broadridge Financial Solutions, Inc. (&#8220;Broadridge&#8221;), Householding Department at 51 Mercedes Way, Edgewood, New York, 11717, or calling 1-866-540-7095. We will deliver promptly a separate copy of the Notice or proxy materials to a shareholder at a shared address to which a single copy was delivered, if requested. If you would like to opt out of householding for future deliveries of proxy materials, please contact your broker, bank or other nominee. </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Beneficial shareholders who share an address and receive multiple copies of the proxy materials but want to receive only a single copy of these materials in the future should contact their broker, bank or other nominee and make this request. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">If you are a registered shareholder or hold your shares in an employee benefit plan, we sent you and each registered or plan shareholder at your address separate Notices or sets of proxy materials. </p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">18.</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">Are my votes confidential? </p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Yes. Your votes will not be disclosed to the directors, officers or employees, except: </p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:9.94%;white-space:nowrap">

<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">as necessary to meet applicable legal requirements and to assert or defend claims for or against us; </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">

<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">

<td valign="top">

<div align="left">

<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>

<div align="left">

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">20.</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">How do I find out the voting results? </p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We expect to announce preliminary voting results at the Annual Meeting. We will disclose final voting results in a Current Report on Form 8-K to be filed with the SEC on or <font style="color:#000000;">before May&#160;21, 2019. The </font>Form 8-K will be available at <font style="font-style:italic;text-decoration:underline;">http://ir.mondelezinternational.com/sec.cfm</font> and on the SEC&#8217;s website at <font style="font-style:italic;text-decoration:underline;">www.sec.gov</font><font style="font-style:italic;">. </font></p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">21.</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">What do I need to do if I want to attend the Annual Meeting? </p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Pre-register by 11:59 p.m. <font style="color:#000000;">EDT on May&#160;14, 2019. </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;letter-spacing:-0.3pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">If you want to bring a guest, you must indicate that when you <font style="color:#000000;">pre-register. Due to space limitations, you may bring only one guest. </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Indicate you intend to attend the Annual Meeting by: </p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:9.94%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">going to &#8220;shareholder meeting registration&#8221; link at </font><font style="font-style:italic;text-decoration:underline;color:#000000;">www.proxyvote.com</font><font style="color:#000000;">; or </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:9.94%;white-space:nowrap">

<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;">following the prompts for meeting attendance on the telephone voting site. </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">To be admitted into the Annual Meeting, you and your guest, if any, must present valid government-issued photographic identification, such as a driver&#8217;s license. </p>

<div align="left">

<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;letter-spacing:-0.1pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;letter-spacing:-0.1pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">23.</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;font-weight:bold;letter-spacing:-0.1pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">May I ask questions at the Annual Meeting? </p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Yes. Shareholders will have the opportunity to ask questions or make comments related to the matters being voted on. They may do so at the times and in the manner indicated in the meeting agenda and meeting procedures that we will distribute at the Annual Meeting registration desk and according to the Chairman&#8217;s instructions. <font style="color:#000000;">We will provide an opportunity for shareholders to make comments or ask additional questions of a general nature about the Company </font>during <font style="color:#000000;">the Questions portion of the Annual Meeting. </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">When asking questions, shareholders will be required to observe the meeting procedures. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:5pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:5pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<td valign="middle"  style="width:94%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:16pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;color:#5A2D82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">2019 Proxy Statement</p></td>
</tr>

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:1pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU100"></a><a name="toc498940_58"></a><font style="font-size:1pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="toc498940_58"></a>&#160; </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;color:#5A2D82;font-size:16pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="N2018_ANNUAL_MEETING_SHAREHOLDERS"></a><a name="N2018_ANNUAL_MEETING_SHAREHOLDERS"></a>2020 Annual Meeting of Shareholders </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We presently anticipate holding the 2020 Annual Meeting of Shareholders on approximately the same date as this year&#8217;s Annual Meeting. </p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;color:#5A2D82;font-family:Arial;font-size:12pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="SHAREHOLDER_NOMINATIONS_PROPOSALS_FOR_20"></a><a name="SHAREHOLDER_NOMINATIONS_PROPOSALS_FOR_20"></a>Shareholder Nominations and Proposals for the 2020 Annual Meeting </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Shareholders should mail all nominations and proposals to the Corporate Secretary at Mondel&#275;z International, Inc., Three Parkway North, Deerfield, Illinois 60015. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">You may obtain a copy of the By-Laws from the Corporate Secretary (please make a written request to the same address) or by visiting <font style="font-style:italic;text-decoration:underline;">www.mondelezinternational.com/investors/corporate-governance</font>. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Shareholder Nominations of a Candidate for Election as a Director or Shareholder Proposal of Business for Considerations at an Annual Meeting of Shareholders (not for inclusion in the Company&#8217;s 2020 proxy materials) </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Under the By-Laws, a shareholder may nominate a candidate for election as a director or propose business for consideration at an annual meeting of shareholders (but, in either case, not for inclusion in the proxy materials) by delivering written notice that contains certain required information to the Corporate Secretary and otherwise complying with other requirements included in our By-Laws. The Corporate Secretary must receive this written notice no later than 120 days, and no earlier than 150 days, before the first anniversary of the preceding year&#8217;s annual meeting. Accordingly, to be considered at the 2020 Annual Meeting of Shareholders, the Corporate Secretary must receive a shareholder&#8217;s written notice of nomination or proposal on or after December&#160;17, 2019 and on or before January&#160;16, 2020. If we change the date of an annual meeting by more than 30 days from the date of the previous year&#8217;s annual meeting, then we must receive this written notice no later than 60 days before the date of the annual meeting. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Shareholder&#160;Director&#160;Candidates&#160;for&#160;Possible&#160;Inclusion&#160;in&#160;the&#160;Company&#8217;s&#160;2020 Proxy&#160;Materials (&#8220;Proxy&#160;Access&#8221;) </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The By-Laws provide for proxy access. A shareholder(s) may nominate and include in the 2020 proxy materials director nominees provided that the shareholder(s) and the nominee(s) satisfy the terms, conditions and requirements specified in the By-Laws. The key parameters are: </p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;"></font><font style="font-style:italic;color:#000000;">Minimum Ownership threshold</font><font style="color:#000000;">: 3% or more of the outstanding Common Stock </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;"></font><font style="font-style:italic;color:#000000;">Ownership Duration</font><font style="color:#000000;">: continuously for at least three years </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;"></font><font style="font-style:italic;color:#000000;">Nominating group size</font><font style="color:#000000;">: a shareholder or a group of up to 20 shareholders </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:7.94%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:3.4%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;color:#4C4C4C;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Arial;font-size:10pt;"><font style="color:#000000;"></font><font style="font-style:italic;color:#000000;">Number of Nominees</font><font style="color:#000000;">: greater of 20% of the Board or 2 nominees </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">To be included in the proxy materials for the 2020 Annual Meeting of Shareholders, the Corporate Secretary must receive the required written notice and required information specified in the By-Laws not less than 120 calendar days prior to the first anniversary date of the mailing date for notice of the prior year&#8217;s annual meeting of shareholders, Accordingly, the Corporate Secretary must receive requests to include shareholder-nominated candidates in the proxy materials for the 2020 Annual Meeting of Shareholders on or before November 30, 2019. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Shareholder Proposals for Possible Inclusion in the Company&#8217;s 2020 Proxy Materials </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Under SEC Rule 14a-8, a shareholder may submit a proposal for possible inclusion in the 2020 proxy materials for an annual meeting of shareholders. The Corporate Secretary must receive the proposal and other required information at our principal executive offices no later than 120 calendar days before the one-year anniversary date of the proxy statement&#8217;s release for the previous year&#8217;s annual meeting. Accordingly, to be considered for inclusion in the proxy materials for the 2020 Annual Meeting of Shareholders, the Corporate Secretary must receive a shareholder&#8217;s submission of a proposal on or before the close of business on November 30, 2019. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;">&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> and Corporate Secretary</p></td>

<p style="margin-bottom:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:2pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#FFFFFF;font-family:Arial;font-size:11pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">95</a></p></td>

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:1pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:right;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU101"></a><font style="font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Annex A</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-family:Arial;font-size:12pt;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="FINANCIAL_MEASURE_DEFINITIONS"></a><a name="FINANCIAL_MEASURE_DEFINITIONS"></a>Financial Measures Definitions </p>
<p style="margin-top:3pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We report our financial results in accordance with U.S. GAAP. However, we use non-GAAP financial measures in making financial, operating and planning decisions and in evaluating our performance. Therefore, we also base financial targets for our Annual Cash Incentive Program and performance share units on non-GAAP and other financial measures. The chart below defines each measure and describes the adjustments to the related GAAP measure (if applicable), modifications to our non-GAAP measures for purposes of our compensation targets and our reasons for using these measures. (See our 2018 Form 10-K for additional information on our Non-GAAP Financial Measures and definitions of terms used in the Definitions column below.) </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<div>
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="center" style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100.02%;">
<tr>
<td valign="bottom"  style="width:20%; border-bottom:solid 1.5pt #5B2B82;">
<p style="margin-top:2pt;line-height:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#5B2B82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Measures</p></td>
<td valign="bottom"  style="padding-left:7.2pt;padding-Right:0pt;padding-Top:0pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:33%; border-bottom:solid 1.5pt #5B2B82;">
<p style="line-height:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#5B2B82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Definitions</p>
<p style="line-height:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#5B2B82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(Including&#160;Adjustment to&#160;GAAP&#160;Measure)</p></td>
<td valign="bottom"  style="padding-left:7.2pt;padding-Right:0pt;padding-Top:0pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:27%; border-bottom:solid 1.5pt #5B2B82;">
<p style="line-height:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#5B2B82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Modifications</p></td>
<td valign="bottom"  style="padding-left:7.2pt;padding-Right:0pt;padding-Top:0pt;padding-Bottom:0pt;width:20%; border-bottom:solid 1.5pt #5B2B82;">
<p style="line-height:10pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;color:#5B2B82;font-size:10pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Rationale</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#EEE9F2" style="width:20%; border-top:solid 1.5pt #5B2B82;">
<p style="margin-bottom:3pt;margin-top:2pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Organic Net Revenue Growth (Annual Cash Incentive Program<br />and Performance Share Units)</p></td>
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#EEE9F2" style="width:33%; border-top:solid 1.5pt #5B2B82;">
<p style="margin-top:2pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:7.2pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Organic Net Revenue is defined as net revenues excluding the impacts of:</p>
<p style="margin-top:3pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:27.3pt;;text-indent:-12pt;;font-size:3pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> <font style="color:#4C4C4C;font-size:8pt;">&#8226;</font><font style="font-size:8pt;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;acquisitions;</font></p>
<p style="margin-top:3pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:27.3pt;;text-indent:-12pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;divestitures</font><font style="font-size:7pt;color:#000000;"><sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(1)</sup></font><font style="color:#000000;">; and</font></p>
<p style="margin-top:3pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:27.3pt;;text-indent:-12pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;currency rate fluctuations (calculated based on prior year&#160;rates)</font><font style="font-size:7pt;color:#000000;"><sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(2</sup><sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">)</sup></font><font style="color:#000000;">.</font></p></td>
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#EEE9F2" style="width:27%; border-top:solid 1.5pt #5B2B82;">
<p style="margin-top:2pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:7.2pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-style:italic;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Organic Net Revenue Growth<font style="font-style:normal;">: Actual results calculated based on the definition of Organic Net Revenue Growth used for each year&#160;of the three-year performance cycle.</font></p></td>
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#EEE9F2" style="width:20%; border-top:solid 1.5pt #5B2B82;">
<p style="margin-top:2pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:7.2pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Reflects the growth rates for our base business by eliminating the impact of certain disclosed one-time factors, facilitating comparisons to prior year(s).</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td valign="top"  style="width:20%;">
<p style="margin-top:2pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Adjusted Gross Margin Percent</p>
<p style="margin-top:2pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(Annual Cash Incentive&#160;Program)</p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="width:33%;">
<p style="margin-top:2pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:7.2pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Adjusted Gross Profit divided by Adjusted Net Revenue, which are defined below:</p>
<p style="margin-top:2pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:7.2pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Adjusted Gross Profit is defined as gross profit excluding the impacts of:</p>
<p style="margin-top:3pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:30pt;;text-indent:-12pt;;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;the Simplify to Grow Program<font style="font-size:7pt;"><sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(3)</sup></font>;</p>
<p style="margin-top:3pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:30pt;;text-indent:-12pt;;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;acquisition integration costs;</p>
<p style="margin-top:3pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:30pt;;text-indent:-12pt;;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;divestiture-related costs;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:3pt;margin-top:3pt;margin-left:30pt;;text-indent:-12pt;;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;operating results from divestitures<font style="font-size:7pt;"><sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(1)</sup></font>;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:30pt;;text-indent:-12pt;;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;mark-to-market impacts from commodity and forecasted currency transaction derivative contracts<font style="font-size:7pt;"><sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(</sup><sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">5</sup><sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">)</sup></font>; and</p>
<p style="margin-top:3pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:30pt;;text-indent:-12pt;;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;incremental expenses related to the 2017 malware incident.</p>
<p style="margin-top:2pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:7.2pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Adjusted Net Revenue is defined as net revenues excluding the impact of: divestitures<font style="font-size:7pt;"><sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(1)</sup>.</font></p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="width:27%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:1pt;margin-top:2pt;margin-left:7.2pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:8pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top"  style="width:20%;">
<p style="margin-top:2pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:7.2pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Indicator of overall business trends and performance, based on what business leaders can control.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#EEE9F2" style="width:20%;">
<p style="margin-top:2pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Defined Operating Income</p>
<p style="margin-top:2pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-weight:bold;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">(Annual Cash Incentive&#160;Program)</p></td>
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#EEE9F2" style="width:33%;">
<p style="margin-top:2pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:7.2pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Adjusted Operating Income is defined as Operating Income excluding the impacts&#160;of:</p>
<p style="margin-top:3pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:22.8pt;;text-indent:-12pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;the Simplify to Grow Program</font><font style="font-size:7pt;color:#000000;"><sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(</sup><sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">3</sup><sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">)</sup></font><font style="color:#000000;">;</font></p>
<p style="margin-top:3pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:22.8pt;;text-indent:-12pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;gains or losses (including non-cash impairment charges) on goodwill and intangible assets;</font></p>
<p style="margin-top:3pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:22.8pt;;text-indent:-12pt;;color:#4C4C4C;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;<font style="color:#000000;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;divestiture</font><font style="font-size:7pt;color:#000000;"><sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(1)</sup></font><font style="color:#000000;"> or acquisition gains or losses&#160;and related <br />divestiture<sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(1)</sup>, acquisition and integration costs;</font></p>
<p style="margin-top:3pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:22.8pt;;text-indent:-12pt;;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;operating income from divestitures<font style="font-size:7pt;"><sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(1)</sup></font>;</p>
<p style="margin-top:3pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:22.8pt;;text-indent:-12pt;;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;remeasurement of net monetary position<sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(4)</sup>;</p>
<p style="margin-top:3pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:22.8pt;;text-indent:-12pt;;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;mark-to-market impacts from commodity and forecasted currency transaction derivative contracts<font style="font-size:7pt;"><sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(</sup><sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">5</sup><sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">)</sup></font>;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:3pt;margin-left:22.8pt;;text-indent:-12pt;;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;impact from resolution of tax matters<font style="font-size:7pt;"><sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(6)</sup></font>;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:3pt;margin-left:22.8pt;;text-indent:-12pt;;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;CEO transition remuneration<font style="font-size:7pt;"><sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(7)</sup></font>;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:3pt;margin-left:22.8pt;;text-indent:-12pt;;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;impact from pension participation changes<font style="font-size:7pt;"><sup style="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(8)</sup></font>; and</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:3pt;margin-left:22.8pt;;text-indent:-12pt;;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#8226;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;incremental expenses related to the 2017 malware incident.</p></td>
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#EEE9F2" style="width:27%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:1pt;margin-top:2pt;margin-left:7.2pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-style:italic;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Defined Operating Income<font style="font-style:normal;">: Defined as Adjusted Operating Income calculated at currency exchange rates utilized in our internal financial planning for 2018.</font></p></td>
<td valign="top"  BGCOLOR="#EEE9F2" style="width:20%;">
<p style="margin-top:2pt;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:7.2pt;;text-indent:0pt;;font-size:8pt;font-family:Arial;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Indicator of overall business trends and performance, based on what business leaders can control.</p></td>
</tr></table></div>
